21
00:03:15,350 --> 00:03:20,480
（拉丁语）...终有一日名扬四海

22
00:03:20,770 --> 00:03:22,730
（拉丁语）吾必另辟一径

23
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:25,590
（拉丁语）自当拔尘于世

24
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:30,740
（拉丁语）终有一日名扬四海

25
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:33,630
（拉丁语）吾必另辟一径

26
00:03:33,650 --> 00:03:36,490
（拉丁语）自当拔尘于世

27
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:41,640
（拉丁语）终有一日名扬四海

28
00:03:42,670 --> 00:03:44,630
（拉丁语）吾必另辟一径

29
00:03:44,650 --> 00:03:47,490
（拉丁语）自当拔尘于世

30
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:52,570
（拉丁语）终有一日名扬四海

31
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:54,190
Repeat.
继续念

32
00:04:22,630 --> 00:04:24,460
Good day, sir.
你好

33
00:04:24,580 --> 00:04:26,120
Good day to you.
姑娘好

34
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:29,050
What brings you to Hewlands?
你来休兰农场来做什么？

35
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,740
I'm tutoring the boys here.
来这里教孩子

36
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,750
The Latin tutor.
教拉丁的先生啊

37
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,050
I've heard of you.
我听说过你

38
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:43,660
What brought you into the garden?
那你来这园里干什么？

39
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,220
Uh...
呃...

40
00:04:48,550 --> 00:04:50,760
It's just a question, master tutor.
我就随便问问 教书先生

41
00:04:50,770 --> 00:04:52,800
Yes, I, uh...
嗯 我 那个...

42
00:04:54,010 --> 00:04:57,040
I suppose the air was fresh out here, and...
就是出来透透气 而且...

43
00:04:57,140 --> 00:05:00,410
uh, I saw you with your bird.
呃 我看到你带着只鸟

44
00:05:00,670 --> 00:05:02,970
- It's a hawk. - Ah.
- 那是只鹰 - 哦

45
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,100
May I?
能上前看看吗？

46
00:05:20,730 --> 00:05:22,900
Don't get too close.
别凑太近

47
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:25,590
He doesn't know you.
他没见过你

48
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,500
Oh.
哦

49
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,900
Hello, boy.
你好 小家伙

50
00:05:42,210 --> 00:05:44,430
Ah.
啊 哈哈哈

51
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:48,590
He likes you.
他喜欢你

52
00:05:51,550 --> 00:05:53,370
What is your name?
你叫什么名字？

53
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:56,620
I shan't tell you.
别打听

54
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:01,090
You shall.
就打听

55
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:06,700
I shan't.
我不说

56
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,990
- You shall. - I won't.
- 你会说的 - 我不会

57
00:06:11,910 --> 00:06:14,220
You'll tell me when we kiss.
等我亲你时你就会说了

58
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:35,060
What are you doing?
你在干什么？

59
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:54,500
Agnes.
安妮丝

60
00:06:57,670 --> 00:06:59,700
My name is Agnes.
我叫安妮丝

61
00:07:00,850 --> 00:07:02,890
Where are you from?
你家哪儿的？

62
00:07:06,850 --> 00:07:09,020
Have I said something?
我说错话了吗？

63
00:07:09,210 --> 00:07:10,780
- Huh? - No.
- 啊？ - 没有

64
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:13,670
- You don't know who I am. - Wait, I wish to see...
- 你不知道我是谁 - 等下 我能去你...

65
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:15,620
You can't see me again.
你别再来找我了

66
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:17,580
Oh.
哦

67
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:26,420
Where have you been?
你去哪儿了？

68
00:07:26,540 --> 00:07:28,070
I was in the field helping Bartholomew.
我下地帮巴塞洛缪

69
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,680
A newborn lamb is unwell.
小羊崽病了

70
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:32,130
Well, I... I went to the field.
好 我也去地里了

71
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:33,780
I did not see you there.
可没见你啊

72
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:37,530
Well, I was there. Tell her, Bartholomew.
我确实在那儿 巴塞洛缪哥 你给她说说

73
00:07:37,590 --> 00:07:38,960
She was there.
她确实在那里

74
00:07:39,220 --> 00:07:41,470
Have you seen the new Latin tutor?
你见过新来的拉丁先生吗？

75
00:07:41,490 --> 00:07:42,710
The glover's son.
就是皮匠的儿子

76
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:45,860
The boys said he just ran out, never returned.
孩子们说他上着上着课跑掉了 就再没回来

77
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:47,310
He was supposed to give them lessons
他是来教书还债的

78
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:49,230
to pay off his father's debts.
还他父亲的债

79
00:07:49,390 --> 00:07:50,530
I haven't seen him.
我没见过他

80
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:52,150
Well, should've known better.
算了 早该料到

81
00:07:52,170 --> 00:07:54,340
Like father, like son.
父子都一个德行

82
00:07:58,990 --> 00:08:01,620
You know, I do believe you are the prettiest girls in the parish.
你们俩可是咱们这教区最美的姑娘

83
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:02,990
- We are. - One day,
- 是的 - 将来...

84
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,110
I shall have my wits about me
会有许多人上门提亲

85
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:07,080
for all the suitors that will come for you.
我亲自把关 准把你们嫁个好人家

86
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:09,390
Agnes is the eldest. She'll marry first.
安妮丝是大姐 还轮不到我们

87
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:12,100
She will not if she keeps running off to the forest
她成天往树林里跑 像个流浪女

88
00:08:12,110 --> 00:08:13,780
like a gypsy.
谁会娶她？

89
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,980
- When they said... - Where have you been?
- 他们说... - 你去哪儿了?

90
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,890
We were expecting you hours ago.
我们都等你好几个钟头了

91
00:08:46,910 --> 00:08:48,280
- I was... - Well?
- 我在... - 说啊

92
00:08:48,290 --> 00:08:49,250
I was working.
我在忙事儿

93
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:50,370
Sit.
坐下

94
00:08:50,650 --> 00:08:51,650
Sit.
快坐下吧

95
00:08:53,470 --> 00:08:55,430
Your supper's near cold.
饭菜都凉了

96
00:08:56,790 --> 00:08:58,050
- Uh, boys, boys! - Hey.
- 别闹 别闹 - 别抢

97
00:08:58,070 --> 00:09:00,330
- Stop. - There's enough for all.
- 住手 - 大家都有份 别抢

98
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:02,150
How go the lessons at Hewlands?
休兰农场那边教得怎么样？

99
00:09:02,170 --> 00:09:03,860
Those boys are no scholars.
那些孩子不是读书的料

100
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:06,150
- I wonder at the notion of all that learning. - Hmm.
- 我就纳闷 他们读书有啥用 - 嗯

101
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:09,280
Latin for boys who will be naught but sheep farmers.
注定务农的孩子学拉丁文？

102
00:09:09,290 --> 00:09:11,100
- It is the putting on of airs. - No, no, no!
- 用来装模做样吗？ - 不 不 不

103
00:09:11,110 --> 00:09:13,290
- That will do! - All right, Gilbert.
- 够了 - 都给你 吉尔伯特

104
00:09:15,010 --> 00:09:17,950
You heard your mother. There's enough for all.
听你娘的 都有份 别争

105
00:09:19,890 --> 00:09:22,460
You speak ill of the boys at Hewlands.
你说休兰那帮孩子不好

106
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:24,350
"They're no scholars."
“不是读书的料”

107
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:26,710
But I tell you something,
可我跟你说 他们将来...

108
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,400
they'll ever be more of a man than you are.
比你更像个男子汉

109
00:09:28,420 --> 00:09:31,200
They are put to honest work, unlike you.
人家将来有正经活 你没有

110
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:34,890
Useless, tradeless, your fancy airs.
你没出息 没手艺 只会装模做样

111
00:09:35,770 --> 00:09:37,470
All that education,
读那么多书

112
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,710
not an ounce of sense.
一点用都没有

113
00:09:40,610 --> 00:09:42,110
I'm tutoring those boys to pay
我这没出息的去教书

114
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,380
your debts to that family, am I not?
不就是替你还那户人家的债吗？

115
00:09:45,090 --> 00:09:47,230
Your immeasurable amount of debt,
你欠休兰家那么多债

116
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:49,420
Didn't I help you... Stop!
要不是我... 住手

117
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:55,800
What of the rest of the family at Hewlands?
休兰那边其他人

118
00:09:55,810 --> 00:09:57,320
Have you met them?
你都见过吗？

119
00:09:58,130 --> 00:09:59,330
The mother only.
只见过那户的母亲

120
00:09:59,340 --> 00:10:01,340
- Not the eldest daughter? - No.
- 那大女儿没见到吗？ - 没有

121
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:06,800
It is said the girl is the child of a forest witch.
大家都说 那姑娘是森林巫婆的后代

122
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,470
I've seen her, wandering the back roads alone
我就见过 她独自走在山路上

123
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,400
with a hawk on her arm.
臂上还有只鹰

124
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:13,730
A hawk at Hewlands?
休兰那儿还有鹰？

125
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:14,790
Yes.
是的

126
00:10:14,810 --> 00:10:18,310
They say she takes him to the forest with her unaccompanied.
传言说她每次进林都是一个人带着那只鹰

127
00:10:18,330 --> 00:10:20,530
Yeah, but are you certain, Eliza?
你确定吗 伊莱莎？

128
00:10:20,730 --> 00:10:24,060
The eldest daughter keeps a hawk, not a servant girl?
那拿着鹰的是长女 不是仆人？

129
00:10:24,070 --> 00:10:26,140
Yes. Yeah.
不是仆人 我确定

130
00:10:53,050 --> 00:10:54,280
Agnes.
安妮丝

131
00:10:58,710 --> 00:11:00,110
Hello.
你好

132
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,900
What are you doing here?
你跑来这儿干什么？

133
00:11:02,920 --> 00:11:04,620
Brought you this.
送你个东西

134
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:07,360
What is it?
这是什么？

135
00:11:07,460 --> 00:11:09,100
It's, uh...
这是...

136
00:11:09,670 --> 00:11:11,960
it's a new glove for your bird.
给你那只鸟的新手套

137
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,510
I have a glove.
我有手套了

138
00:11:21,410 --> 00:11:22,440
Agnes.
安妮丝

139
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,620
Agnes, wait.
安妮丝 别跑

140
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:32,350
I know who you are.
我认出你了

141
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,820
Who am I?
那好 我是谁？

142
00:11:33,830 --> 00:11:36,560
Well, I... I don't know you, but I've heard things...
好吧 不算了解你 只是听到些传言...

143
00:11:36,570 --> 00:11:38,680
I'm the daughter of a forest witch?
说我是森林巫婆的女儿？

144
00:11:38,690 --> 00:11:39,890
Yes. People say that, but I-I don't care...
是啊 村里这么说 但我 我不在意...

145
00:11:39,910 --> 00:11:42,050
I am my mother's daughter.
我可是我母亲的女儿

146
00:11:42,790 --> 00:11:45,310
I've learnt many things from her.
从她那儿学的本事多着呢

147
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,300
What are you looking at?
你瞎看什么？

148
00:11:49,310 --> 00:11:50,750
- You. - Why?
- 看你 - 为什么？

149
00:11:57,230 --> 00:12:00,040
- I... - I thought you were a man of words, master tutor.
- 因... - 你这教书的 不该能言善辩吗？

150
00:12:00,060 --> 00:12:01,990
Yes.
是的

151
00:12:02,150 --> 00:12:04,180
- Are you not? - Jus...
- 还难住你了？ - 只是...

152
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:07,600
Speaking with people is sometimes difficult for me.
我有时很难直接跟人说话

153
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:11,240
Well, tell me a story, then.
好 那就讲个故事吧

154
00:12:12,010 --> 00:12:14,080
- A story? - Yes.
- 讲故事？ - 对

155
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:18,820
What story would you like?
你想听什么故事？

156
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:28,970
Something that moves you.
起码能打动你自己的故事

157
00:12:32,180 --> 00:12:33,810
All right.
好吧

158
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:38,970
Do you know the story of Orpheus and Eurydice?
你知道俄耳甫斯和欧律狄刻的故事吗？

159
00:12:38,980 --> 00:12:41,740
{\an8}【译注: 古希腊神话】

160
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:43,810
Orpheus is...
俄耳甫斯这个男人

161
00:12:43,820 --> 00:12:46,360
a man of music.
有着天赋异禀的音乐才能

162
00:12:46,370 --> 00:12:49,200
He has this exquisite voice.
他还有着天籁般的嗓音

163
00:12:49,890 --> 00:12:52,740
His playing of the kithara, which is a...
他弹那种七弦里拉 是...

164
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:54,660
is-is a harp-like lyre,
是类似竖琴的乐器

165
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:56,730
is so divine,
声音美得妙不可言

166
00:12:57,980 --> 00:12:59,950
birds, the...
连天上的鸟儿 地...

167
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:03,560
the beasts, e-even the stones and the trees,
地上的走兽 甚 甚至石头和树

168
00:13:03,570 --> 00:13:08,290
they all moved to the rhythm of his music.
都能被他的音乐打动随之起舞

169
00:13:08,810 --> 00:13:13,540
Now, Orpheus falls in love with this beautiful nymph, Eurydice.
后来 俄耳甫斯爱上了一位美丽的山林少女 叫欧律狄刻

170
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:16,530
Soon after their marriage,
和山林少女刚结完婚

171
00:13:16,540 --> 00:13:18,640
Eurydice's bitten by a viper
她就被毒蛇咬了

172
00:13:18,650 --> 00:13:21,430
and poison courses through her body,
毒素在她体内迅速扩散

173
00:13:21,450 --> 00:13:23,300
and she's killed.
她就此身亡

174
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:27,890
And Orpheus, filled with grief,
俄耳甫斯悲痛欲绝

175
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:30,940
journeys to the underworld to take her back.
下到冥府想要将她带回

176
00:13:31,980 --> 00:13:36,730
He charms this three-headed dog, Cerberus.
他用琴声迷住了守门的三头犬 刻耳柏洛斯

177
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:40,480
He beguiles Hades until finally...
甚至感动了冥王哈得斯 最终...

178
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,160
...he's allowed to take his love back with him
冥王同意了

179
00:13:43,170 --> 00:13:46,040
to the world of the living but...
允许把这名女子带回人间 但...

180
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:49,110
...under one condition.
但有一个条件

181
00:13:49,130 --> 00:13:50,670
What is it?
什么条件？

182
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,640
She must follow behind him,
这名女子必须跟在他身后

183
00:13:53,660 --> 00:13:56,500
and he must not turn around to look at her.
而他绝对不能回头看

184
00:13:59,870 --> 00:14:03,610
Now, as they begin their ascent,
现在 他们开始往人间走

185
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:07,560
Orpheus can't hear her footsteps, so he listens...
俄耳甫斯却听不见他妻子的脚步声 于是他听啊...

186
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:13,490
...and listens and listens and listens.
听啊 听啊 一直听

187
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:19,190
But all he can hear is the sound of his heartbeat.
他只听得见自己的心跳

188
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:28,250
And the rest is silence.
余下的只有沉寂

189
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:35,790
And as he approaches the gates of the underworld...
当他快到冥门出口时

190
00:14:40,130 --> 00:14:42,280
...he can't contain himself any longer.
他忍不住了

191
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:45,440
He turns around to look at her, and she is...
他回头去看妻子 然后妻子...

192
00:14:47,060 --> 00:14:49,370
...trapped in the underworld forever.
永远被困在冥府里了

193
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,710
Hmm.
嗯

194
00:15:05,660 --> 00:15:07,320
That was a good story.
这是个好故事

195
00:15:07,330 --> 00:15:09,170
Did you like it?
你喜欢吗？

196
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:16,930
Remember, mugwort, what you brought to pass,
艾草者 古之名药也

197
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:19,850
{\an8}【《九草咒》: 古英语药咒 列九种草药以驱毒治疫】

198
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:19,690
what you readied at Regenmeld.
世人皆知其德 传颂至今

199
00:15:19,850 --> 00:15:23,140
You're called Una, the most ancient plant.
其名曰艾 为草之首

200
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:26,140
You defy three, you defy 30,
能驱三疾 能制三十疾

201
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:28,270
you defy venom, you defy air illness,
能解毒气 能散瘴疠

202
00:15:28,290 --> 00:15:31,180
you defy the horror that stalks the land.
能降瘟疫 克之而胜

203
00:15:31,190 --> 00:15:34,120
And you, waybread, plant mother,
车前草者 草之母也

204
00:15:34,140 --> 00:15:36,980
you're open to the east yet mighty within.
根植东方 性禀刚毅

205
00:15:36,990 --> 00:15:40,880
Carts creeped over you, women rode over you.
遭车碾而不折 遇众踏而复起

206
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:44,130
You withstood it all, and you pushed back.
刚柔相济 疗人间之疾苦

207
00:15:44,380 --> 00:15:47,190
Is it true that you know everything about a person
你真的能靠摸一个人的手

208
00:15:47,210 --> 00:15:49,210
by touching them here?
看透一切吗？

209
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:51,320
Not everything.
并非全部

210
00:15:51,330 --> 00:15:53,350
When you touched me here, what did you see?
你摸我时你看到了什么？

211
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,530
I saw a landscape.
我看见了一幅画面

212
00:15:55,550 --> 00:15:57,850
- You saw a landscape? - Mm-hmm.
- 一幅画？ - 嗯

213
00:15:59,350 --> 00:16:04,020
Spaces, caves, cliff tops,
空洞 黑洞 裂口

214
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:07,590
tunnels and oceans,
暗道和深海

215
00:16:07,780 --> 00:16:11,590
this deep, dark, black void,
深不见底 一片漆黑的虚空

216
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:14,610
undiscovered countries.
未知的国度

217
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:21,290
（拉丁语）天道有常 宿命有律

218
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:21,300
{\an8}【译注: 正在朗读《农事诗》第一卷】

219
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:27,010
（拉丁语）万物难逃衰落之数 消亡乃其必然

220
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:32,420
（拉丁语）天道有常 宿命有律

221
00:16:32,430 --> 00:16:38,020
（拉丁语）万物难逃衰落之数 消亡乃其必然

222
00:16:39,350 --> 00:16:41,520
She speaks...
她说话了...

223
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:45,810
She speaks, she speaks.
她说话了 她说话了

224
00:16:46,450 --> 00:16:47,810
But, soft,
且慢

225
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:51,070
what light through yonder window breaks?
那窗户透出来的是什么光？

226
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:58,410
It is the east, and Juliet is the sun...
那是东方 朱丽叶就是太阳...

227
00:16:59,180 --> 00:17:02,620
...and kill...
赶走那....

228
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:09,440
...the envious moon.
嫉妒的月亮

229
00:17:09,460 --> 00:17:11,970
{\an8}【译注: 正在创作《罗密欧与朱丽叶》第二幕第二场】

230
00:17:25,950 --> 00:17:27,430
Hello.
你好

231
00:17:28,220 --> 00:17:29,220
Hello.
你好

232
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,460
I wish to be handfasted to you.
我要和你成亲

233
00:17:46,470 --> 00:17:49,330
No, I... I must be handfasted to you.
不 我 我必须和你成亲

234
00:17:49,350 --> 00:17:51,050
No one else will do.
非你不可

235
00:17:51,060 --> 00:17:53,270
I-I will speak with your stepmother and your brother,
我会去跟你继母和你哥哥说

236
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:55,510
and of course they will not agree, but...
估计他们不会答应

237
00:17:57,520 --> 00:18:01,080
I don't care because I have no talent for waiting.
不管行不行就这么定了 不能等了

238
00:18:03,150 --> 00:18:05,820
I cannot abide waiting.
哪怕是私定终身

239
00:18:06,610 --> 00:18:07,870
What about your parents?
那你父母怎么办？

240
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,940
Your parents will never agree.
他们绝不会答应的

241
00:18:11,580 --> 00:18:13,180
Follow me.
跟我来

242
00:18:57,950 --> 00:19:00,490
Wait. Wait. W-Wait.
等 等 等下

243
00:19:12,500 --> 00:19:13,970
- No! - No!
- 跑不掉了 - 别

244
00:19:24,340 --> 00:19:25,810
My glove.
我的手套

245
00:19:27,530 --> 00:19:30,640
- This is my mother's glove. - Hmm.
- 是我母亲留给我的 - 哦

246
00:19:31,470 --> 00:19:34,000
She came out of the woods...
她源于森林

247
00:19:35,130 --> 00:19:37,170
...like her mother
就像她的母亲一样

248
00:19:37,180 --> 00:19:39,450
and her mother before her.
像她母亲的母亲一样

249
00:19:45,210 --> 00:19:49,420
The women in my family see things...
我家族女人能看到些...

250
00:19:49,430 --> 00:19:51,640
...that others don't.
别人看不到的东西

251
00:19:53,810 --> 00:19:55,280
Agnes.
安妮丝

252
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:01,500
Remember, mugwort,
艾草者 古之名药也

253
00:20:01,520 --> 00:20:04,910
what you brought to pass, what you readied at Regenmeld.
世人皆知其德 传颂至今

254
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:07,750
You're called Una, the most ancient plant.
其名曰艾 为草之首

255
00:20:07,770 --> 00:20:09,820
You defy three, you defy 30,
能驱三疾 能制三十疾

256
00:20:09,830 --> 00:20:12,460
you defy venom, you defy air illness,
能解毒气 能散瘴疠

257
00:20:12,470 --> 00:20:15,140
you defy the horror that stalks the land.
能降瘟疫 克之而胜

258
00:20:15,620 --> 00:20:17,750
Bartholomew, it will heal.
巴塞洛缪 会好的

259
00:20:18,590 --> 00:20:20,090
Will it make a scar?
会留疤吗？

260
00:20:20,100 --> 00:20:23,200
It may. That's no bad thing.
可能会 但并非坏事

261
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:24,900
Listen.
听

262
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,990
Do you hear that?
听见了么？

263
00:20:31,290 --> 00:20:34,800
You must pay attention to your dreams, Agnes.
留心你的梦 安妮丝

264
00:20:35,810 --> 00:20:37,740
They will always guide you.
梦永远会指引你

265
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:03,000
- Good day. - Good day.
- 你们好 - 你也好

266
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,290
Yes.
好

267
00:21:20,390 --> 00:21:22,840
Agnes, what's, uh...
安妮丝 你怎么在...

268
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,940
what's happened?
你怎么在这儿？

269
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:28,100
Her mother has banished her from their house.
她母亲把她逐出家门了

270
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,720
She's not my mother.
她不是我生母 而且...

271
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:32,950
The house belongs to my brother, Bartholomew.
我家那房子归我哥哥巴塞洛缪

272
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:35,100
I chose to leave.
我是自愿离开的

273
00:21:35,930 --> 00:21:37,550
She's with child.
她有身孕了

274
00:21:37,560 --> 00:21:38,510
Oh.
哦

275
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:40,750
Says it's yours.
还说孩子是你的

276
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:45,320
- Is it? Yours? - Uh...
- 真的吗？真是你的吗？ - 呃...

277
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:48,690
The child in her belly, did you put it there?
她肚子里的孩子 是你弄的吗？

278
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:51,860
I did.
是我

279
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,810
- We are handfasted, Mother. - We will never allow it!
- 我们已经私定了 娘 - 休想

280
00:21:54,830 --> 00:21:56,750
- There is no sin in it. - I'm afraid you will need
- 这有什么错啊 - 没我们的同意

281
00:21:56,770 --> 00:21:58,700
- our consent, and we will... - There is no sin in it!
- 你成不了亲的 - 这有什么错啊

282
00:21:58,720 --> 00:22:01,280
- ...we will never give it, ever! - All right!
- 我们决不允许这桩婚事 - 行 行

283
00:22:03,100 --> 00:22:04,660
What?
啥？

284
00:22:05,340 --> 00:22:07,580
- You've been bewitched. - No.
- 你被她蛊惑了 - 不是的

285
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:16,410
I'd rather you went to sea than marry this wench.
我宁愿你当水手送命 也别娶这个巫婆

286
00:22:16,470 --> 00:22:17,870
Mary.
玛丽

287
00:22:18,790 --> 00:22:20,760
There's no need for that.
不必这样

288
00:22:21,320 --> 00:22:24,550
I have no doubt we can come to an arrangement.
既然他们两厢情愿 这事好解决

289
00:22:24,570 --> 00:22:26,410
- John. - Hush, woman.
- 约翰 - 安静 女人

290
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:30,770
I am certain you are eager
你肯定想在教堂里

291
00:22:30,780 --> 00:22:33,320
to see your sister before the altar.
看到你妹妹出嫁吧

292
00:22:34,410 --> 00:22:36,510
I'm certain you'd rather not see your boy
我肯定想现在

293
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:38,360
dragged before the bawdy court.
控告你儿子奸淫

294
00:22:38,380 --> 00:22:40,520
There's no need for that.
没必要闹成那样

295
00:22:40,540 --> 00:22:43,180
They said they are handfasted.
他们都已经私定了

296
00:22:44,270 --> 00:22:46,060
Only if I say so.
嫁不嫁由我说了算

297
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:51,180
But why marry a pasty-faced scholar? What use is he?
嫁给那白面书生到底有啥好处？他有什么用

298
00:22:51,190 --> 00:22:56,200
He's got more inside of him than any man I've ever met.
他的内心比我见过的任何人都深邃

299
00:22:58,380 --> 00:23:00,610
Everything will change.
人心是会变的

300
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:03,700
You. You will change.
你 你也不例外

301
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,460
I'm already changing.
我的心已经变了

302
00:23:05,470 --> 00:23:07,490
It's too quiet in there.
里头太静了

303
00:23:07,810 --> 00:23:09,800
In where?
哪儿里头？

304
00:23:09,820 --> 00:23:11,600
That house.
他们家

305
00:23:11,740 --> 00:23:15,640
What would our mother say to us if we were afraid or uncertain?
记得我们害怕迷茫时 娘怎么劝咱的吗？

306
00:23:16,630 --> 00:23:19,570
To live with our hearts open.
我们要敞开心扉

307
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:23,980
To shut it not in the dark
别叫它躲在黑暗里

308
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:27,260
but to turn it to the sun.
而是转向太阳

309
00:23:27,550 --> 00:23:31,830
He loves me for what I am, not what I ought to be.
他爱的是我本色 不图我变成谁

310
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:35,990
Then marry him you shall.
那就嫁给他吧

311
00:23:41,020 --> 00:23:42,190
Thank you.
谢谢

312
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:45,420
Remember, mugwort...
艾草者 古之名药也

313
00:23:46,540 --> 00:23:48,310
Say it with me. Say it with me.
来 说跟我一起说 一起说

314
00:23:48,390 --> 00:23:50,310
What you brought to pass,
世人皆知其德

315
00:23:50,330 --> 00:23:52,740
what you readied at Regenmeld.
传颂至今

316
00:23:52,750 --> 00:23:57,010
You are called Una, the most ancient plant.
其名曰艾 为草之首

317
00:23:59,320 --> 00:24:03,800
You defy three, you defy 30,
能驱三疾 能制三十疾

318
00:24:04,130 --> 00:24:08,550
you defy venom, you defy air illness,
能解毒气 能散瘴疠

319
00:24:08,850 --> 00:24:11,860
you defy the horror that stalks the land.
能降瘟疫 克之而胜

320
00:24:38,330 --> 00:24:40,260
Look at me.
回头看我

321
00:24:41,180 --> 00:24:42,790
Look at me.
回头看我

322
00:27:00,730 --> 00:27:02,420
Agnes.
安妮丝

323
00:28:52,490 --> 00:28:53,840
Hey.
嘿

324
00:28:55,110 --> 00:28:57,960
Look. Look at that. Look at the fire.
看 看那光 那是火

325
00:28:57,980 --> 00:29:00,250
Mmm, what's that?
看看 那是什么啊

326
00:29:00,390 --> 00:29:02,350
The doggy dragged something in.
是小狗叼进来的东西

327
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:04,060
There's something.
快看

328
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:05,840
Oh.
哦

329
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:09,570
Daddy's coming.
你爹回来了

330
00:29:10,110 --> 00:29:11,310
Hello.
回来了

331
00:29:34,150 --> 00:29:37,190
Stitches need to be smaller.
针脚要小一点

332
00:29:37,260 --> 00:29:39,490
M-Much smaller.
再小 再小一点

333
00:29:40,460 --> 00:29:41,750
Yes.
对

334
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:47,760
Hmm.
哼

335
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:50,280
Useless.
没出息

336
00:29:54,370 --> 00:29:57,000
Okay, and now...
好 再小点

337
00:29:57,280 --> 00:29:58,680
smaller.
再小点

338
00:30:00,300 --> 00:30:02,730
- Where are you going? - I'm going.
- 你去哪儿？ - 我要出去

339
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:04,780
Get back to work.
回去干活

340
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:19,640
That was the last time you will ever hit me.
这是你最后一次打我

341
00:30:19,650 --> 00:30:21,160
Do you understand?
明白吗？

342
00:30:21,180 --> 00:30:23,420
- Do you understand?! - Yes.
- 明白吗？ - 明白

343
00:30:46,370 --> 00:30:48,630
My love, you should come back to bed.
爱人 该睡觉了

344
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:57,090
What are you writing?
你在写什么？

345
00:30:57,110 --> 00:30:58,850
Nothing of note.
不值一提

346
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:00,650
It's never nothing.
总有值得称道的地方

347
00:31:00,670 --> 00:31:02,100
I don't know.
还没写好呢

348
00:31:02,310 --> 00:31:05,680
Perhaps when it's finished, it will...
也许写完会好...

349
00:31:07,290 --> 00:31:09,160
Perhaps when it's finished.
也许吧

350
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:11,080
Why don't you read me what you've written?
念给我听听吧

351
00:31:11,090 --> 00:31:12,610
A-Agnes, it's not--
安妮丝 这还没...

352
00:31:12,630 --> 00:31:14,520
It-It's not finished.
还没写好呢

353
00:31:16,920 --> 00:31:19,150
It's not finished.
没写好

354
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:31,500
Stop it. You'll wake the baby.
别敲了 吵醒孩子了

355
00:31:33,550 --> 00:31:34,530
It's okay.
好了

356
00:31:34,540 --> 00:31:36,810
No. It's okay.
不哭 不哭

357
00:31:42,470 --> 00:31:43,680
I'm sorry.
对不起

358
00:31:48,530 --> 00:31:50,430
I've had too much, uh...
我喝多了

359
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:53,390
Agnes, I've had too much to drink.
安妮丝 我喝多了

360
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:57,720
I've had...
我喝...

361
00:32:00,510 --> 00:32:02,940
I've had too much to drink.
我喝的太多了

362
00:32:12,410 --> 00:32:13,580
Hey.
嘿

363
00:32:15,150 --> 00:32:17,160
What is it?
有什么心事吗？

364
00:32:19,030 --> 00:32:20,690
Give me your hand.
我给你的手看看

365
00:32:20,710 --> 00:32:22,730
Pl-Pl-Please, please, please, please,
别 别 别 别 别

366
00:32:22,750 --> 00:32:24,520
please, please, please, please.
别 别 求你了 别

367
00:32:24,530 --> 00:32:26,200
- What are you afraid I will see? - Please stop.
- 你怕我看见什么吗？ - 求你了 别

368
00:32:26,220 --> 00:32:28,350
That I am a violent and dangerous man.
我怕我将来会伤害你

369
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:29,750
No, you are none of those things.
不会 你不是那样的人

370
00:32:29,770 --> 00:32:31,640
- How do you know? - You're a good man. You're a...
- 你怎么能肯定？ - 你是个好人 你是个...

371
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:35,460
You are a good man.
你是个好人

372
00:32:36,740 --> 00:32:38,970
You're a good man.
你是个好人

373
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:45,980
Is it that you wish that we never wed?
难道是后悔跟我结婚了吗？

374
00:32:48,950 --> 00:32:51,150
How could you say such a thing?
怎么能说出这种话？

375
00:32:51,240 --> 00:32:53,570
How could you say such a thing?
你怎么能说出这种话？

376
00:32:57,620 --> 00:33:00,870
You and Susanna are all that I live for.
我活着就是为了你和苏珊娜

377
00:33:00,890 --> 00:33:02,680
All that I live for.
我活着就是为了你们

378
00:33:02,700 --> 00:33:04,970
- What is it, then? - This...
- 那到底怎么回事？ - 是...

379
00:33:09,910 --> 00:33:11,870
- Here. Look at me. - Just stop!
- 来 把手给我 - 停下

380
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:14,750
Stop, stop. Please, please, please, please, please, please.
停 停 求你停下 停 停 停

381
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:16,290
Look at me.
看着我

382
00:33:16,310 --> 00:33:18,940
Listen. Listen. Listen.
听着 听着 听我说

383
00:33:25,370 --> 00:33:27,840
I'm lost.
我迷失了

384
00:33:30,920 --> 00:33:33,090
I've lost my...
我找不...

385
00:33:33,100 --> 00:33:35,130
I've lost my way.
我找不到方向了

386
00:33:39,930 --> 00:33:43,340
I just need to-- uh, Agnes, I just need to work.
我需要 我需要静下心好好写作 安妮丝

387
00:33:44,820 --> 00:33:46,600
He's not sleeping.
他都睡不着觉

388
00:33:46,610 --> 00:33:49,220
- Has he ever lost his temper with you? - No.
- 他对你发火了吗？ - 没有

389
00:33:49,230 --> 00:33:51,920
- If he raises a hand... - No, he has never. He's never.
- 要是他对你动手.... - 没有 他从没那样 从没那样

390
00:33:51,930 --> 00:33:54,220
 He's angry with himself.
他只是为自己懊恼

391
00:33:54,230 --> 00:33:56,430
He's sick with himself.
心里难受得要命

392
00:33:56,450 --> 00:33:57,700
He's a good man.
他是个好人

393
00:33:57,720 --> 00:33:59,130
He's a good husband, he's a good father,
是个好丈夫 也是个好父亲

394
00:33:59,150 --> 00:34:01,030
but he n-needs more.
但他还需要更多

395
00:34:01,050 --> 00:34:03,530
What could he possibly need other than his family and you?
他已经有了家和你 还能需要什么？

396
00:34:03,540 --> 00:34:05,900
- He has you. - He needs to go to London.
- 他已经有了你 - 他需要去伦敦

397
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:08,150
- London? - Yeah.
- 伦敦？ - 是的

398
00:34:08,850 --> 00:34:09,700
Why London?
为啥去伦敦？

399
00:34:09,720 --> 00:34:11,740
Because London is where the whole world gathers.
因为伦敦汇聚天下

400
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:13,950
Perhaps he could extend his father's business there.
说不定能把他爹的手艺带去发扬光大

401
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:15,580
- Oh, you're being hasty again. - Who knows what he may be...
- 哎 你又冲动了 - 谁知道他将来会怎样

402
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:17,300
I'm not being hasty. He needs more.
我不是冲动 他需要更多

403
00:34:17,310 --> 00:34:18,250
- Well, he needs proper work. - He's not of this world.
- 他只是太闲了 - 他不该呆这小地方

404
00:34:18,270 --> 00:34:19,640
The man needs proper work.
给他找个活儿忙起来

405
00:34:19,660 --> 00:34:21,130
- What's in this little town? - He can't just run away.
- 这小地方能有什么出路？ -  他不能就这么跑掉

406
00:34:21,140 --> 00:34:22,930
This little life? This little thing, it'll...
这小日子 这小地方

407
00:34:22,940 --> 00:34:24,420
...crush him.
会逼疯他的

408
00:34:25,260 --> 00:34:27,130
He needs distance from his father.
他得离他爹远点

409
00:34:27,150 --> 00:34:28,420
And you would go with him to London?
你跟他一起去伦敦吗？

410
00:34:28,430 --> 00:34:30,310
No, I'll wait until he's settled.
不 等他安顿好再说

411
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:31,850
There'll be more of us soon.
马上家里就会多一口人

412
00:34:31,860 --> 00:34:33,270
- Another child? - Yes.
- 又怀上了？ - 是的

413
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:35,470
By summer's end.
夏末时候生

414
00:34:36,170 --> 00:34:37,750
Then now is not the time to send him away.
那现在更不能把他送走了

415
00:34:37,770 --> 00:34:39,470
I'll lose him.
那我会失去他的

416
00:34:40,070 --> 00:34:41,510
I'm already losing him.
我已经在失去他了

417
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:42,630
You'll lose him if you send him away.
要是送他走 就彻底失去他了

418
00:34:42,640 --> 00:34:46,060
No, I know, I know that our love will keep us steady.
不 不会的 我肯定我俩的爱能维系得住

419
00:34:46,150 --> 00:34:48,800
Please. Will you speak to his father?
求你了 替我跟他爹说说吧

420
00:34:48,820 --> 00:34:52,310
He'll listen to you if you suggest him going to London.
要是你跟他提去伦敦的事 他会听你的

421
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:53,890
Please.
求你了

422
00:34:56,520 --> 00:34:58,890
I should find lodgings.
我得找个住处

423
00:34:58,910 --> 00:35:01,430
Be near the river, close to the tanneries.
最好靠河的 离河边皮革场近点

424
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:04,110
But I'm told that the currents in the river are dangerous
我听说那河水很急

425
00:35:04,130 --> 00:35:07,190
and that you must engage an experienced boatman
过河要请有经验的船夫

426
00:35:07,210 --> 00:35:09,510
every time you cross, and I'll be certain to do that every time,
每次过河我都照办

427
00:35:09,530 --> 00:35:11,570
I promise.
我保证

428
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:13,710
And I will think of you and Susanna
我会时时刻刻

429
00:35:13,730 --> 00:35:15,250
with every passing moment.
挂念你和苏珊娜的

430
00:35:15,260 --> 00:35:16,830
And I will find us lodgings in London,
我会给咱们找个好住处

431
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:18,880
and we shall all be together again.
到时候在伦敦团聚

432
00:35:24,830 --> 00:35:27,060
Do you still not know if it's a boy or a girl?
你还没预见出是男孩还是女孩吗？

433
00:35:27,070 --> 00:35:28,190
No.
没有

434
00:35:28,210 --> 00:35:29,850
Don't know why.
我也说不清为什么

435
00:35:30,540 --> 00:35:32,470
Have you not said that you would always have two children?
你不是说过会有两个孩子陪你到最后吗？

436
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:34,020
Yes.
是的

437
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:36,390
Two children at my deathbed.
临终前会有两个孩子在身边

438
00:35:36,900 --> 00:35:40,330
Well, then, here is the second.
第二个能陪你到最后的人来了

439
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:52,230
- We won't say goodbye. - No.
- 咱们就别道别了 - 好

440
00:35:57,910 --> 00:36:00,300
You get-- Go.
别磨蹭了 快走吧

441
00:36:35,420 --> 00:36:37,620
- You going somewhere? - No, I'm just...
- 你要出门吗？ - 不是 我只是...

442
00:36:37,990 --> 00:36:38,920
Yes, I'm going to the lake...
对 我要去湖边走走...

443
00:36:38,940 --> 00:36:40,970
You're not going to the forest.
你不许进森林

444
00:36:44,610 --> 00:36:47,020
- I must. - No, you must not. Gilbert!
- 我非去不可 - 不 你不许去 吉尔伯特快来

445
00:36:47,030 --> 00:36:49,830
You... you have to let me go there.
你 你得让我去那里

446
00:36:50,080 --> 00:36:52,080
- Let me go there! - Listen Agnes.
- 你必须让我走 - 听我说 安妮丝

447
00:36:52,100 --> 00:36:54,630
- You must let me go! - The river has burst its banks!
- 你得放我去 - 河堤已经决口了

448
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:55,870
- Let me! - There is no way...
- 让我去 - 外面很危险

449
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:57,720
- There's no way to get to the forest. - Let me! No!
- 根本没路去森林那边 - 放我走 不要

450
00:36:57,730 --> 00:36:59,360
- We have everything ready for you. - My baby!
- 我们都为你准备好了 - 我孩子

451
00:36:59,380 --> 00:37:00,980
No, my-my baby.
不 我 我孩子

452
00:37:16,470 --> 00:37:17,910
I can't.
我不行

453
00:37:19,210 --> 00:37:20,960
It isn't coming out.
生不出来

454
00:37:21,450 --> 00:37:23,890
I will not have my baby in this house.
我没法在这屋里生孩子

455
00:37:23,900 --> 00:37:25,270
Not in this house.
没法在这屋

456
00:37:25,510 --> 00:37:26,540
No.
没法

457
00:37:30,110 --> 00:37:31,350
The river.
河水

458
00:37:31,360 --> 00:37:32,750
- Hush, hush, hush, hush. Hush. - No, no, no, no.
- 使劲儿 使劲儿 使劲儿 - 不 不 不

459
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:33,980
He spoke about the river.
他说要住河边

460
00:37:33,990 --> 00:37:36,550
The river is dangerous. He may be swept downstream!
河很危险 他可能会被冲走

461
00:37:38,350 --> 00:37:40,200
Agnes. Agnes.
安妮丝 安妮丝

462
00:37:40,710 --> 00:37:43,650
Agnes. Agnes, all is well with him.
安妮丝 安妮丝 他一切安好

463
00:37:43,750 --> 00:37:45,910
Do you not recall his last letter?
你难道忘了他最近的信吗？

464
00:37:45,930 --> 00:37:47,060
Stop the screaming.
别叫了

465
00:37:47,070 --> 00:37:48,270
You'll wake the whole town.
会把整村人都吵醒的

466
00:37:48,280 --> 00:37:49,390
He sound...
他语气...

467
00:37:49,410 --> 00:37:51,010
He sounded different.
他语气不对

468
00:37:51,030 --> 00:37:53,230
No, he had good news for us.
不 他带来的是好消息

469
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:54,520
- The theater. - Theater.
- 剧院 - 剧院

470
00:37:54,540 --> 00:37:56,980
He has a contract with the players
他和剧团定下来了

471
00:37:56,990 --> 00:37:59,100
- to make gloves for the theater. - the theater
- 做剧院用的手套 - 剧院

472
00:38:00,550 --> 00:38:02,190
Agnes, hush now.
安妮丝 使劲儿

473
00:38:02,470 --> 00:38:03,850
Hush. Hush. Hush.
使劲儿 使劲儿 使劲儿

474
00:38:03,870 --> 00:38:05,110
Bear down. Bear down.
用力 用力

475
00:38:10,140 --> 00:38:11,200
Ah! Ooh!
来了 来了

476
00:38:11,220 --> 00:38:13,070
- There we go. - It's a boy.
- 出来了 - 是个男孩

477
00:38:13,080 --> 00:38:15,190
There we go.
真好

478
00:38:15,390 --> 00:38:18,330
Good boy. Good boy.
乖孩子 乖孩子

479
00:38:22,020 --> 00:38:24,260
It's a boy.
是个男孩

480
00:38:27,290 --> 00:38:29,050
It's a boy.
是个男孩

481
00:38:30,660 --> 00:38:32,120
My boy.
我的儿子

482
00:38:34,520 --> 00:38:35,980
Thank you.
谢谢你

483
00:38:50,360 --> 00:38:52,390
What is it? What's happening?
怎么回事？怎么了？

484
00:38:52,500 --> 00:38:54,370
She's starting again.
她又要生了

485
00:38:54,690 --> 00:38:56,880
- You're having twins, my girl. - Come on, Eliza.
- 姑娘啊 你怀的是双胞胎 - 来 伊莱莎

486
00:38:56,890 --> 00:38:59,230
Here. Quickly.
快 抱着他

487
00:39:00,380 --> 00:39:01,410
Take him.
抱好

488
00:39:05,670 --> 00:39:07,090
No, no, no.
不 不 不

489
00:39:07,100 --> 00:39:09,700
Two standing at my deathbed.
我临终前会有两个孩子在身边

490
00:39:10,970 --> 00:39:12,890
I always believed that it would be...
我一直以为...

491
00:39:12,900 --> 00:39:15,650
that they would be my children.
一直以为是长大的孩子

492
00:39:15,940 --> 00:39:17,660
And now...
现在我...

493
00:39:17,670 --> 00:39:19,410
now I see it will be you.
我明白了 原来就是你们俩

494
00:39:19,430 --> 00:39:20,760
We need to get you to the stool.
得把你扶到产凳上

495
00:39:20,780 --> 00:39:22,150
It's coming. It's here.
快生了 要生了

496
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:24,310
- No. - Come on. Come on up. Up, up.
- 不要 - 来 来 起来 起来

497
00:39:24,330 --> 00:39:26,440
Please. I can't... I...
别 我 我不行

498
00:39:26,450 --> 00:39:27,660
I can't.
我不行

499
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:29,570
- Go. - I should never have...
- 来 - 我不该...

500
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:31,320
I can't...
我不行了...

501
00:39:33,740 --> 00:39:35,170
I can't make it.
我挺不过去了

502
00:39:35,190 --> 00:39:37,070
I got it wrong. I got it wrong.
我弄错了 我弄错了

503
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:38,980
I got it...
我弄错...

504
00:39:39,380 --> 00:39:41,810
He... He's not here.
他 他不在

505
00:39:41,820 --> 00:39:44,060
He's... He's not here.
他 他不在这里

506
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:47,260
Agnes, you can...
安妮丝 你能行的

507
00:39:47,380 --> 00:39:49,240
and you must.
你必须行

508
00:39:49,250 --> 00:39:51,280
I cannot.
我不行

509
00:39:53,020 --> 00:39:54,080
Agnes.
安妮丝

510
00:39:55,380 --> 00:39:57,150
You can...
你能行的

511
00:39:57,170 --> 00:39:58,930
and you will.
你会挺过去的

512
00:40:00,060 --> 00:40:04,730
Your husband was born here in this room.
你丈夫就在这间屋里出生

513
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:09,140
He took his first breath there by the window.
他就在那窗边 第一次呼吸

514
00:40:11,030 --> 00:40:12,910
Please.
求求你

515
00:40:14,190 --> 00:40:16,060
Please let this child live.
求求你 保住孩子

516
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:18,820
Let this child live. Please.
一定保孩子 一定

517
00:40:18,950 --> 00:40:20,490
Will you let him...
让他...

518
00:40:20,630 --> 00:40:23,700
Let him come back and be with his child.
让他回到家后能有孩子陪他

519
00:40:24,500 --> 00:40:25,760
Please.
求你了

520
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:28,440
Let him think kindly of me always.
让他对我留个好念想

521
00:40:28,450 --> 00:40:29,580
Remember me.
记着我

522
00:40:31,070 --> 00:40:32,600
Mama.
娘

523
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:34,500
Mama.
娘

524
00:40:34,700 --> 00:40:36,500
Mum?
娘？

525
00:40:43,390 --> 00:40:45,180
Just too weak.
她没抗住

526
00:40:45,190 --> 00:40:47,350
She was in too much pain.
她承受了很大的痛苦

527
00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:48,690
I mean, poor woman.
太可怜了

528
00:40:48,700 --> 00:40:50,950
She just got weaker and weaker.
越来越痛 她承受不住了

529
00:40:50,960 --> 00:40:52,460
I mean, that's just the way of it sometimes.
有时候命就是这样

530
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:54,210
She-she must have known the end was nigh.
她 她大概早就知道这一刻了

531
00:40:54,220 --> 00:40:56,650
Best not speak of her to the children.
最好别跟孩子提起她了

532
00:40:57,100 --> 00:40:59,520
Safer with a different mother.
再娶一个吧

533
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:02,620
So young.
孩子都还小

534
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:04,440
They may not remember her.
兴许能忘掉

535
00:41:05,740 --> 00:41:07,500
- Mum! - Agnes. Agnes.
- 娘啊 - 安妮丝 安妮丝

536
00:41:07,510 --> 00:41:09,450
- Mama, no! - No, no. Agnes.
- 娘啊 不 - 不 不 安妮丝

537
00:41:09,460 --> 00:41:10,830
Child. Child.
孩子 孩子

538
00:41:10,850 --> 00:41:13,240
- Mummy, no! - No, no, no. Ch-Ch-Ch-- No.
- 娘 不要 - 不 不 孩子 孩子 不行

539
00:41:13,250 --> 00:41:14,450
- No! - No.
- 放开我 - 不行

540
00:41:14,470 --> 00:41:16,550
- No, let me see her! - No, no!
- 不 让我见娘 - 不 不

541
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:18,220
- Let me see her! - No!
- 我要见娘 - 不

542
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:19,870
No, Mama!
不 娘

543
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:21,510
- Agnes. - No!
- 安妮丝 - 不

544
00:41:22,950 --> 00:41:25,860
Mum. I want, I want my mum.
娘 我要我娘 我要我娘

545
00:41:26,810 --> 00:41:28,470
I want my mum...
我要我娘啊...

546
00:41:54,650 --> 00:41:56,520
Oh! Here we go! It's a girl!
来了 是个女孩

547
00:41:56,540 --> 00:41:58,670
It's a girl. She's...
是个女孩 她...

548
00:41:58,910 --> 00:42:00,650
- It's... Wait. - What?
- 等等... - 怎么了？

549
00:42:05,590 --> 00:42:06,830
Come on. Come on.
快点 快点

550
00:42:06,850 --> 00:42:08,780
Why is she not crying?
她怎么不哭？

551
00:42:10,900 --> 00:42:12,660
Why is she not crying?
她怎么不哭？

552
00:42:12,790 --> 00:42:14,630
She lives not.
她没活过来

553
00:42:14,650 --> 00:42:15,650
Let me have her.
让我抱抱

554
00:42:15,670 --> 00:42:17,480
You should not look upon her. It's bad luck.
不行 这不吉利

555
00:42:17,490 --> 00:42:18,470
Give her to me.
把她给我

556
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:19,660
I'll make sure it gets a decent burial.
我会把她安葬妥当的

557
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:21,670
Give me my child!
把我孩子给我

558
00:42:21,690 --> 00:42:25,100
{\an8}【双胞胎: 当时双胞胎被视为怪异现象和不祥征兆】

559
00:42:25,110 --> 00:42:26,830
My child.
我的孩子啊

560
00:42:29,620 --> 00:42:33,360
Agnes, you have a baby boy.
安妮丝 你有个儿子

561
00:42:35,240 --> 00:42:38,240
Let me bring him to you, and you may feed him.
我把他抱来 你可以喂他

562
00:42:39,980 --> 00:42:42,210
The girl has gone to heaven.
女孩已经去了天国

563
00:42:44,980 --> 00:42:47,270
She's not gone to heaven.
她不会去天国的

564
00:42:48,860 --> 00:42:51,800
I made a vow the night my mother died.
我母亲去世那晚我发过誓

565
00:42:53,250 --> 00:42:57,090
I will go to your church, but I shan't say a word there.
我会去你们的教堂 但别指望我开口说什么

566
00:42:53,250 --> 00:42:57,110
{\an8}【译注: 当时无宗教自由 故以含蓄方式表达不信教】

567
00:43:36,340 --> 00:43:38,670
Yes. Yes. Yes.
太好了 太好了 太好了

568
00:43:47,720 --> 00:43:49,810
You will live.
你会活下去的

569
00:43:51,560 --> 00:43:53,520
You will live.
你会活下去的

570
00:43:54,530 --> 00:43:59,400
I will make sure nothing ever takes you away.
我会保护你到底 绝不放手

571
00:44:20,630 --> 00:44:22,910
I actually couldn't find it.
我怎么都找不到

572
00:44:32,000 --> 00:44:33,430
Hmm.
没有

573
00:44:36,290 --> 00:44:37,760
Here.
找到了

574
00:44:38,610 --> 00:44:39,980
Perfect.
太好了

575
00:44:40,940 --> 00:44:42,770
I found my hat.
找到帽子了

576
00:44:49,180 --> 00:44:51,380
Okay. Yes.
来 对

577
00:44:56,470 --> 00:44:58,670
Okay, take that side. Take that side.
来 转过去 转过去

578
00:44:58,700 --> 00:45:00,000
Yeah.
好

579
00:45:00,140 --> 00:45:02,520
And put it around here.
然后系好

580
00:45:04,550 --> 00:45:06,120
Perfect.
完美

581
00:45:09,250 --> 00:45:11,540
- Ooh. Sorry. - Let me help you.
- 哎呀 - 我来吧

582
00:45:17,570 --> 00:45:19,500
It's down my face.
挡到我脸了

583
00:45:27,090 --> 00:45:30,060
- I'm Hamnet. - I'm Hamnet.
- 跟我学“我是哈姆奈特” - “我是哈姆奈特”

584
00:45:31,130 --> 00:45:34,770
- I'm Judith. - I'm Judith.
- “我是珠迪丝” - “我是珠迪丝”

585
00:45:35,880 --> 00:45:37,750
There will be no running in this house.
屋里不准跑

586
00:45:38,460 --> 00:45:42,120
Conduct yourselves, please, as...
你们要举止端正 要像...

587
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:44,560
gentlewomen and gentlemen.
淑女与绅士

588
00:45:47,390 --> 00:45:48,810
Where are you going?
你们要去哪儿？

589
00:45:48,820 --> 00:45:51,720
Yeah. He's-he's coming. He's coming.
对 他来了 他来了

590
00:45:54,500 --> 00:45:55,580
Hello.
回来了

591
00:45:55,590 --> 00:45:57,030
Hello.
你回来了

592
00:45:57,480 --> 00:45:59,620
We all know they've swapped clothes.
一看就知道他俩对调了衣服

593
00:45:59,630 --> 00:46:01,410
How long are we going to pretend we don't?
咱们什么时候揭穿？

594
00:46:01,420 --> 00:46:03,550
We'll pretend for as long as they think they're the same.
只要他们继续演 咱们就不揭穿

595
00:46:05,640 --> 00:46:06,870
Hi.
你好

596
00:46:12,250 --> 00:46:14,070
Father, will you help me with the Greek passage
爹 能再教我下

597
00:46:14,080 --> 00:46:15,750
from yesterday's lesson?
昨天那段希腊文吗？

598
00:46:15,770 --> 00:46:18,270
Hamnet, I thought you'd already learnt it.
哈姆奈特 你不是会背了吗？

599
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:20,940
I didn't because I left my primer at school.
我忘了 因为把课本落学堂了

600
00:46:20,950 --> 00:46:22,430
Well, Hamnet,
好吧 哈姆奈特

601
00:46:22,450 --> 00:46:23,750
you need to take your studies seriously.
你要用心学

602
00:46:23,770 --> 00:46:25,140
How do you expect to improve if you're not...
不努力怎么会进步...

603
00:46:25,150 --> 00:46:29,520
（希腊语）吾不肯苟且而生 不甘平庸而逝

604
00:46:25,150 --> 00:46:29,570
{\an8}【译注: 正在朗读荷马《伊利亚特》第22卷】

605
00:46:29,570 --> 00:46:34,600
（希腊语）愿成就丰功伟绩 令后世永传吾名

606
00:46:29,570 --> 00:46:34,610
{\an8}【《伊利亚特》: 荷马(古希腊诗人)史诗 论英雄 战争与命运】

607
00:46:35,380 --> 00:46:36,800
You rascals.
你们这群小淘气

608
00:46:36,820 --> 00:46:39,540
- Did we trick you? - Of course you did.
- 我们耍到你了吗？ - 当然了

609
00:46:39,550 --> 00:46:42,100
You swapped places to hoodwink me again.
你们又互换来耍我

610
00:46:42,120 --> 00:46:45,790
{\an8}【译注: 当时女性普遍无法接受正规教育 现实中他妻女都不识字】

611
00:46:45,800 --> 00:46:47,130
Susanna, come here.
苏珊娜 过来

612
00:46:47,140 --> 00:46:49,100
Come here.
快过来

613
00:46:52,250 --> 00:46:55,090
Now, do you remember the thing we were going to do for your mother?
你们还记得要给娘准备的那件事吗？

614
00:46:55,100 --> 00:46:56,590
- Yeah. - You remember? You ready to do it?
- 嗯 - 都记得吗？准备好了吗？

615
00:46:56,610 --> 00:46:58,370
- Yeah. - Okay. Go outside quickly.
- 嗯 - 好 快去 快去准备

616
00:46:58,390 --> 00:47:01,450
Go, go, go, go, go.
快去 快去 快去

617
00:47:02,990 --> 00:47:04,620
- Just step toward... - Wait.
- 朝前走 - 别急

618
00:47:04,640 --> 00:47:06,740
One st-- Come to your right. Step.
再走 往右走 小心

619
00:47:06,960 --> 00:47:09,270
Step. One more.
慢点 再迈一步

620
00:47:09,290 --> 00:47:10,720
- What. - One more.
- 啥 - 再迈一步

621
00:47:18,400 --> 00:47:21,370
When shall we three meet again?
咱们三个儿啥时候再聚？

622
00:47:21,390 --> 00:47:24,580
In thunder, lightning or in rain?
等打雷 等闪电 还是等下雨？

623
00:47:24,600 --> 00:47:28,950
When hurly-burly's done, when the battle's lost and won!
等到这场吵闹都停了 等到这一仗打出个输赢了

624
00:47:28,960 --> 00:47:32,960
That will be ere at set of sun.
那就在太阳落山以前

625
00:47:33,650 --> 00:47:35,950
- Where the place? - Upon the heath.
- 在什么地方？ - 就在荒原

626
00:47:36,320 --> 00:47:38,320
There to meet with Agnes.
在那儿同安妮丝会面

627
00:47:38,330 --> 00:47:39,910
I come, Graymalkin.
我来了 灰妖猫

628
00:47:39,920 --> 00:47:41,580
Paddock calls.
蛤蟆叫

629
00:47:41,840 --> 00:47:43,250
Anon!
马上到

630
00:47:43,580 --> 00:47:45,480
Fair is foul and foul is fair.
美即是丑 丑即是美

631
00:47:45,500 --> 00:47:48,860
Fair is foul and foul is fair. Fair is foul and foul is fair.
美即是丑 丑即是美 美即是丑 丑即是美

632
00:47:48,870 --> 00:47:50,680
Fair is foul and foul is fair.
美即是丑 丑即是美

633
00:47:50,870 --> 00:47:51,860
Hover through the...
穿入到...

634
00:47:51,880 --> 00:47:54,360
{\an8}【《麦克白》: 出自第一幕第一场 参考卞之琳译本】

635
00:47:54,370 --> 00:47:55,440
Well done!
演得好

636
00:47:55,450 --> 00:47:57,690
That was amazing!
真精彩

637
00:47:57,800 --> 00:48:00,320
Dig it deep, and then you move all of it to the side,
挖深点 把土拨到一边

638
00:48:00,330 --> 00:48:02,240
and then you put it down here.
然后把根放进去

639
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:05,150
Right? And then you get the soil around the sides,
明白吧 然后把土填回去

640
00:48:05,410 --> 00:48:07,480
and then you pat it more.
用手把土拍平

641
00:48:08,240 --> 00:48:10,840
And then you get bits like that.
然后手上就沾了土

642
00:48:15,490 --> 00:48:17,810
And you rub it in your hands.
然后两手搓一搓

643
00:48:17,870 --> 00:48:20,130
Whoa. And then back!
等下 向后退

644
00:48:20,380 --> 00:48:21,760
Do this.
照我这样做

645
00:48:21,770 --> 00:48:24,040
And when you're doing this, circle.
然后转圈 盯住对手

646
00:48:24,280 --> 00:48:26,110
Yeah, like that.
对 就是这样

647
00:48:26,120 --> 00:48:27,480
Ready?
准备好了吗？

648
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:29,650
Forward. And back.
前进 后撤

649
00:48:29,730 --> 00:48:31,740
Now, parry, parry, parry.
现在 挡剑 挡剑 挡剑

650
00:48:32,950 --> 00:48:35,410
Good. Again.
很好 再来

651
00:48:36,430 --> 00:48:38,820
Now, after that one, I'm gonna do this,
接着 我出这招

652
00:48:38,830 --> 00:48:40,070
and you get out of the way.
你要闪开

653
00:48:40,090 --> 00:48:42,200
Ready? Circle off. Spin your sword.
准备好了吗？绕圈走 转动你的剑

654
00:48:42,290 --> 00:48:43,490
No.
不对

655
00:48:43,610 --> 00:48:45,950
Circle, spin your sword.
绕圈 把剑转起来

656
00:48:46,200 --> 00:48:48,100
Now, come forward.
现在 向前迈

657
00:48:48,700 --> 00:48:50,110
And go back.
再往后退

658
00:48:50,120 --> 00:48:52,020
One, two three.
挡剑三次

659
00:48:52,030 --> 00:48:53,260
Out of the way!
闪开

660
00:48:53,270 --> 00:48:54,410
Very good. Again.
非常好 再来一次

661
00:48:54,570 --> 00:48:56,200
Judith, what's this one called?
珠迪丝 闻闻这是什么？

662
00:48:56,210 --> 00:48:57,440
- Thyme. Thyme. - Rosemary.
- 百里香 百里香 - 是迷迭香

663
00:48:57,460 --> 00:48:59,440
-Thyme. - Thyme. Thyme.
- 是百里香 - 好吧 百里香 百里香

664
00:49:01,220 --> 00:49:03,260
- I got it mixed up. - That's okay.
- 我记错了 - 没关系

665
00:49:03,280 --> 00:49:05,590
This one...
这株是...

666
00:49:05,750 --> 00:49:07,910
- Now, that's rosemary. - Yeah.
- 这是迷迭香 - 对

667
00:49:08,070 --> 00:49:09,820
And what is rosemary for?
迷迭香有什么用处？

668
00:49:09,840 --> 00:49:11,880
- Putting it in apples. - Apples.
- 放在苹果里一起炖 - 炖苹果

669
00:49:11,890 --> 00:49:13,500
No. What is Rosemary's for?
不对 再闻闻

670
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:14,760
- Remembering. - Remembering.
- 记忆 - 纪念

671
00:49:14,780 --> 00:49:16,420
Remembering.
对 记忆纪念

672
00:49:56,090 --> 00:49:59,320
Now, you're to rub all this in your hands.
现在 搓一搓

673
00:50:01,770 --> 00:50:03,980
You blow a little wish.
吹个小心愿进去

674
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:08,450
To wish him on his way.
许个愿 让他带走

675
00:50:08,740 --> 00:50:11,730
Yeah? And it's your secret with him.
明白吗？这就是你和他的小秘密了

676
00:50:18,970 --> 00:50:21,040
Did you see him?
看见了吗？

677
00:50:21,350 --> 00:50:23,810
Did you not see him in the sky?
没看见他在天上吗？

678
00:50:24,060 --> 00:50:26,180
All right, do it again.
好 再来一次

679
00:50:26,200 --> 00:50:27,900
Make another wish.
再许个愿

680
00:50:30,750 --> 00:50:32,290
Look. Right up there.
看 就在上面

681
00:50:33,260 --> 00:50:35,530
Look, just there. Did you see him?
就在那里 看见了吗？

682
00:50:36,880 --> 00:50:41,220
And he's got all your wishes tucked in his little heart.
他把你们所有的愿望都藏在他的小心窝里了

683
00:50:41,250 --> 00:50:43,690
So any time that you want to remember him,
每当想念他的时候

684
00:50:43,760 --> 00:50:46,130
you just have to go...
只要吹一下...

685
00:50:47,330 --> 00:50:49,700
Where are you going?
你要去哪儿？

686
00:50:49,830 --> 00:50:52,940
Huh? I'm gonna catch you!
我来抓你了

687
00:50:52,990 --> 00:50:54,680
I'm gonna catch you!
我来抓你了

688
00:50:59,470 --> 00:51:01,000
Father?
爹？

689
00:51:05,590 --> 00:51:07,320
Is all well?
没事吧？

690
00:51:07,410 --> 00:51:08,780
Yes.
没事

691
00:51:12,840 --> 00:51:15,900
Listen, I want you to stay away from your grandfather.
听着 别太靠近你爷爷

692
00:51:16,060 --> 00:51:18,560
He'll not hit your sisters, but it's you that I worry for,
他不会打你姐妹 但我担心你

693
00:51:18,570 --> 00:51:21,200
and I need to know that you'll be safe when I'm not here.
当我走了你要能保护好自己

694
00:51:21,220 --> 00:51:23,330
You're going back to London again?
又要回伦敦了么？

695
00:51:23,340 --> 00:51:24,580
Yes, tomorrow.
对 明天

696
00:51:24,740 --> 00:51:26,350
Tomorrow?
明天就走？

697
00:51:26,370 --> 00:51:27,940
It's all right.
没关系的

698
00:51:29,290 --> 00:51:31,170
Will we go with you this time?
这次我们能跟你一起去吗？

699
00:51:31,180 --> 00:51:32,780
No, not yet.
不行 还不行

700
00:51:35,680 --> 00:51:37,030
Hey.
嘿

701
00:51:40,380 --> 00:51:41,880
I'll miss you.
我会想念你的

702
00:51:43,020 --> 00:51:45,790
But I have to go, you understand? I...
但我得走 你明白吗？我得...

703
00:51:46,400 --> 00:51:47,840
I know.
我懂

704
00:51:48,400 --> 00:51:49,970
I understand.
我明白

705
00:51:51,740 --> 00:51:53,110
That's good.
那就好

706
00:51:54,460 --> 00:51:56,840
'Cause I need you to look after your mother and your sisters.
你要替我照顾好你娘和你姐妹

707
00:51:56,850 --> 00:51:58,270
Will you do that?
能做到吗？

708
00:51:58,290 --> 00:51:59,490
Yes.
能

709
00:51:59,710 --> 00:52:01,210
- Will you be brave? - Yes.
- 能做个男子汉吗？ - 能

710
00:52:01,290 --> 00:52:02,850
Yes?
真的吗？

711
00:52:03,160 --> 00:52:05,170
- Will you be brave? - Yes.
- 你勇敢吗？ - 是

712
00:52:05,180 --> 00:52:06,700
Will you be brave?!
是男子汉吗？

713
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:09,100
- Huh?! - Yes! Yes, I'll be brave!
- 是吗？ - 是 是 我是男子汉

714
00:52:09,120 --> 00:52:12,430
I'll be brave. I'll be brave.
我很勇敢 我是男子汉

715
00:52:14,970 --> 00:52:17,990
I've looked at houses for us in London.
我已经在伦敦替咱们物色好房子了

716
00:52:20,140 --> 00:52:22,640
-Autumn is coming. - Mm.
- 秋天就要来了 - 嗯

717
00:52:23,510 --> 00:52:25,740
And the children will fall ill.
孩子们会生病的

718
00:52:27,970 --> 00:52:30,670
Judith, she's still not strong enough.
珠迪丝还是太虚弱了

719
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:34,490
She often gets congestion in her chest.
她常常胸闷

720
00:52:34,600 --> 00:52:37,100
And the air in London is...
伦敦那空气...

721
00:52:37,120 --> 00:52:38,540
We can't.
去不了

722
00:52:38,950 --> 00:52:41,850
But one day soon, we will.
但迟早有一天 我们会去的

723
00:52:42,730 --> 00:52:45,160
We will come to London with you.
我们会跟你去伦敦的

724
00:52:46,270 --> 00:52:48,000
No, you won't.
不会的

725
00:52:49,030 --> 00:52:51,320
You'll never come.
你永远不会来的

726
00:52:51,940 --> 00:52:55,180
You've waited for the heat of summer to pass...
夏天你嫌太热

727
00:52:56,290 --> 00:52:58,480
...the dryness of autumn,
秋天干燥

728
00:52:59,560 --> 00:53:01,830
the snow and the cold.
冬天太冷

729
00:53:03,100 --> 00:53:06,530
You do not believe that Judith will ever survive London.
你压根儿不信珠迪丝能在伦敦活着

730
00:53:07,900 --> 00:53:11,360
You'd do anything in your power to keep that child alive.
你会想尽一切办法保住那孩子

731
00:53:11,370 --> 00:53:13,340
Isn't that what a mother is supposed to do?
做母亲的不就该这样吗？

732
00:53:13,360 --> 00:53:15,520
Of course it is.
当然是

733
00:53:15,530 --> 00:53:16,900
So...
所以...

734
00:53:20,280 --> 00:53:26,020
...I've decided to look for land outside Stratford.
我决定就在这镇子附近给咱们找个家

735
00:53:27,250 --> 00:53:30,110
That's where you should live with the children.
你和孩子们还在斯特拉特福镇这片生活

736
00:53:27,250 --> 00:53:31,900
{\an8}【斯特拉特福: 距离伦敦160公里 当时为羊毛 皮革等畜产品加工地】

737
00:53:31,900 --> 00:53:33,300
- Thank you. - Mm-hmm.
- 谢谢你 - 嗯

738
00:53:37,020 --> 00:53:38,740
Ooh!
来吧

739
00:53:39,080 --> 00:53:40,620
Where is she? Ah!
快过来 啊

740
00:53:45,630 --> 00:53:48,530
Hamnet. There he is.
哈姆奈特呢 你来了

741
00:53:51,540 --> 00:53:53,140
Come here.
过来吧

742
00:53:58,450 --> 00:54:00,860
I love you. I love you. I love you.
爱你 爱你 爱你

743
00:54:02,290 --> 00:54:04,680
All right. Love you.
行了 来亲一下

744
00:54:06,630 --> 00:54:08,530
- Come on. - Love you.
- 好了 - 亲一下

745
00:54:10,080 --> 00:54:11,810
Love you.
亲一下

746
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:13,580
Oh.
哦

747
00:54:15,970 --> 00:54:18,170
All right. Come here.
好吧 过来

748
00:54:19,150 --> 00:54:21,920
- Remember what I told you, okay? - Okay.
- 还记得我告诉你的话吗？ - 记得

749
00:54:23,630 --> 00:54:25,290
Good boy.
好孩子

750
00:54:27,130 --> 00:54:29,000
- Bye. - Bye.
- 我要走了 - 再见

751
00:54:33,360 --> 00:54:35,120
- Bye. - Bye.
- 走了 - 再见

752
00:54:37,230 --> 00:54:39,800
- Bye. - Bye.
- 真走了 - 再见

753
00:54:58,800 --> 00:55:00,530
Hamnet?
怎么了 哈姆奈特？

754
00:55:09,150 --> 00:55:11,720
Come on. Come here.
过来 到这儿来

755
00:55:16,660 --> 00:55:18,530
Show me your hand.
把手给我

756
00:55:19,630 --> 00:55:21,730
What? What do you see?
你 你看到什么了？

757
00:55:23,220 --> 00:55:25,290
I see you.
我看到你...

758
00:55:26,030 --> 00:55:27,600
Grown.
长大了

759
00:55:29,300 --> 00:55:31,060
And very strong.
身强力壮

760
00:55:31,920 --> 00:55:34,990
And I see you in London working with your father.
我还看到你在伦敦 和你父亲一起工作

761
00:55:37,460 --> 00:55:39,500
- In the theater? - Yes.
- 在剧院吗？ - 对

762
00:55:39,520 --> 00:55:41,210
At the playhouse.
在剧场

763
00:55:43,990 --> 00:55:45,710
What will I be doing?
我会在那儿做什么？

764
00:55:45,730 --> 00:55:47,750
What do you wish to do, Hamnet?
你想做什么呢？

765
00:55:47,770 --> 00:55:51,670
I should be one of the players with a sword.
我想当个拿剑的演员

766
00:55:51,800 --> 00:55:53,400
A sword?
拿剑的？

767
00:55:53,420 --> 00:55:54,700
Yes.
对

768
00:55:54,710 --> 00:55:57,710
And I shall clash it against the sword of the other player.
我想拿剑和其他演员交锋

769
00:55:58,500 --> 00:56:00,570
Show me.
示范给我看看

770
00:56:01,030 --> 00:56:02,760
There'll be a terrible fight,
会有场激烈的战斗

771
00:56:02,770 --> 00:56:07,060
and everybody watching will be frightened out of their wits.
观众看得心惊胆战

772
00:56:07,680 --> 00:56:09,460
And who will win?
那谁会赢呢？

773
00:56:09,480 --> 00:56:11,030
I shall, of course.
自然是我

774
00:56:11,040 --> 00:56:13,040
Of course you shall.
当然是你

775
00:56:24,810 --> 00:56:27,040
Something has upset them.
它们被什么惊到了

776
00:56:28,050 --> 00:56:30,320
What could it be?
怎么回事？

777
00:56:31,310 --> 00:56:32,970
The weather?
可能是天气

778
00:56:32,980 --> 00:56:35,060
Something in the air, perhaps?
或者空气里有什么 不确定

779
00:56:36,910 --> 00:56:39,790
Best tell Joan to keep the children inside today.
告诉琼今天别让孩子们出门了

780
00:59:29,760 --> 00:59:31,230
Judith?
珠迪丝？

781
00:59:36,140 --> 00:59:37,900
Judith?
珠迪丝？

782
00:59:38,110 --> 00:59:39,670
Where are you?
你在哪儿呢？

783
00:59:42,810 --> 00:59:44,130
Wake up!
醒醒啊

784
00:59:44,150 --> 00:59:46,820
The baker told me her cat had kittens.
面包师的猫生小猫咪了

785
00:59:46,910 --> 00:59:48,730
We need to see them.
咱们得去看看

786
00:59:55,420 --> 00:59:58,260
There's eight, Judith. Eight!
有八只呢 珠迪丝 八只

787
00:59:58,550 --> 01:00:00,950
We need to hurry. It's going to rain.
得抓紧了 要下雨了

788
01:00:04,600 --> 01:00:06,130
Judith?
珠迪丝？

789
01:00:07,570 --> 01:00:09,110
Jude?
小珠？

790
01:00:12,250 --> 01:00:13,960
What's wrong?
你怎么了？

791
01:00:16,790 --> 01:00:18,370
What's wrong, Judith?
哪儿不舒服？珠迪丝

792
01:00:18,390 --> 01:00:20,260
Judith, answer me.
你说话啊 珠迪丝

793
01:00:21,620 --> 01:00:23,140
Judith, wake up.
起来啊

794
01:00:23,600 --> 01:00:25,370
Judith, please. Judith.
求你了 珠迪丝 说句话

795
01:00:40,060 --> 01:00:42,490
- What is it? - It's Judith.
- 怎么了？ - 是珠迪丝

796
01:00:49,150 --> 01:00:50,450
How long has she been like this?
她这样多久了？

797
01:00:50,460 --> 01:00:52,490
Since I returned from school.
我从学堂回来她就这样了

798
01:00:55,540 --> 01:00:56,690
Oh, my God.
天呐

799
01:00:56,700 --> 01:00:58,480
She's got it.
她得上了

800
01:00:58,550 --> 01:01:00,210
Hasn't she?
是不是？

801
01:01:00,230 --> 01:01:02,600
She's got the pestilence.
她得了瘟疫

802
01:01:02,890 --> 01:01:04,660
Hasn't she, Mama?
是不是 娘？

803
01:01:04,670 --> 01:01:06,050
Go find your grandmother.
去找你奶奶

804
01:01:06,060 --> 01:01:07,520
Bid her to come.
让她马上来

805
01:01:07,540 --> 01:01:08,940
Now!
快去

806
01:01:16,560 --> 01:01:17,590
She's burning up.
她烧得厉害

807
01:01:17,610 --> 01:01:20,010
We need, um, more water.
得要水 要很多水

808
01:01:20,030 --> 01:01:21,770
Make a bigger fire and heat up more water.
烧大火 把水烧热了

809
01:01:21,790 --> 01:01:24,000
- We need warm water. - Eliza, fetch more water
- 需要热水 - 伊莱莎 去打些水来

810
01:01:24,020 --> 01:01:25,210
and bring the Bellis from the kitchen.
把厨房的白雏菊也拿来

811
01:01:25,220 --> 01:01:26,730
A row of cinnamon.
再拿肉桂

812
01:01:26,740 --> 01:01:27,920
Cinnamon, that's good for drawing out the heat.
肉桂能退烧

813
01:01:27,940 --> 01:01:29,570
Pineweed or a rue. Thyme, yes.
还要松草或者芸香 百里香也要

814
01:01:29,580 --> 01:01:31,110
You'll find them in the room.
去屋里找

815
01:01:31,130 --> 01:01:32,540
- Mama. Yeah. - The other table. The other side.
- 娘啊 - 屋里那张桌子边 桌子边

816
01:01:32,550 --> 01:01:33,920
Yeah, Mama's here, my love.
娘在这儿呢 我的心肝

817
01:01:33,940 --> 01:01:36,370
Here, drink this. It's rosemary and jelly.
来 喝这个 迷迭香熬的药膏

818
01:01:36,380 --> 01:01:38,960
All will be well, hmm?
会没事的 听到没

819
01:01:38,980 --> 01:01:40,280
All will be well.
都会没事的

820
01:01:40,300 --> 01:01:42,240
Judith, stay with.
珠迪丝 坚持住

821
01:01:42,380 --> 01:01:44,980
Mama's here. It's okay. Mama's here.
娘在这儿 没事的 娘在这儿

822
01:01:45,420 --> 01:01:47,190
Rhubarb. We need rhubarb to purge the stomach,
大黄 得要大黄 能清肠子

823
01:01:47,200 --> 01:01:48,190
drive out the pestilence.
能驱瘟疫

824
01:01:48,210 --> 01:01:50,220
Can you go and fetch some?
你能去取吗？

825
01:01:50,530 --> 01:01:52,770
Mama's here. It's okay. Judith, we're all here.
娘在这儿 没事的 珠迪丝 大家都在

826
01:01:52,780 --> 01:01:54,290
Susanna, draw some water, too.
苏珊娜 你也去打些水来

827
01:01:54,300 --> 01:01:56,080
Hamnet and... and Mary and Susanna.
哈姆奈特和玛丽还有苏珊娜

828
01:01:56,090 --> 01:01:57,760
Draw water as soon as you can.
快去打水

829
01:01:57,810 --> 01:01:59,680
Why isn't he here?
他怎么还没来呢？

830
01:02:00,660 --> 01:02:03,390
Eliza, go write to your brother and tell him to come.
伊莱莎 去给你哥哥威廉写信 让他赶快回来

831
01:02:06,780 --> 01:02:08,150
Judith.
珠迪丝

832
01:02:10,310 --> 01:02:12,550
Open your mouth, Judith.
张开嘴 珠迪丝

833
01:02:12,570 --> 01:02:15,640
Open your mouth. Mama's here. That's it.
张开嘴 娘在这儿 对 很好

834
01:02:15,650 --> 01:02:17,300
That's good.
好孩子

835
01:02:17,310 --> 01:02:19,010
Yes, you'll be safe.
对 会没事的

836
01:02:19,350 --> 01:02:21,610
You'll open your mouth. Drink it down.
张开嘴 都喝下去

837
01:02:21,760 --> 01:02:25,020
Swallow it down. Mama's here. It's okay, Judith.
喝下去 娘在这儿 别怕 珠迪丝

838
01:02:26,330 --> 01:02:28,590
Mama's here. It's okay.
娘在这儿 别怕

839
01:02:28,600 --> 01:02:29,710
Okay.
没事的

840
01:02:57,630 --> 01:02:58,890
Agnes.
安妮丝

841
01:02:59,990 --> 01:03:01,350
Agnes.
安妮丝

842
01:03:01,970 --> 01:03:04,630
You have done all that you can.
你已经尽力了

843
01:03:07,320 --> 01:03:09,660
I will not let her cross over.
我绝不会放手的

844
01:03:22,820 --> 01:03:27,010
Grandmama, you had three daughters that were taken.
奶奶 你失去的三个女儿...

845
01:03:30,970 --> 01:03:32,600
Were they...
也是像...

846
01:03:34,550 --> 01:03:36,280
Were they like Judith?
也是像珠迪丝这样吗？

847
01:03:39,360 --> 01:03:41,170
Anne was seven.
安妮那时七岁

848
01:03:43,390 --> 01:03:45,770
The other two were just babies.
另两个还只是吃奶的婴儿

849
01:03:46,060 --> 01:03:48,760
They all had swellings and...
都长了肿块...

850
01:03:46,060 --> 01:03:50,430
{\an8}【腺鼠疫: 会导致淋巴结肿大 常见于颈部 腋下和腹股沟】

851
01:03:50,440 --> 01:03:52,750
...fever like Judith.
都发高烧 跟珠迪丝一样

852
01:03:52,940 --> 01:03:55,370
Your mother's trying to...
你娘在...

853
01:03:55,520 --> 01:03:57,720
keep a grip on her child.
拼命想保住她的孩子

854
01:03:58,500 --> 01:04:00,370
It won't work.
没用的

855
01:04:03,620 --> 01:04:07,020
What is given may be taken away at any time.
命是天给的 随时都能被收回

856
01:04:09,900 --> 01:04:12,470
We must never let our guard down.
我们得时刻提防着

857
01:04:13,720 --> 01:04:16,480
Never take for granted...
千万别把孩子们的...

858
01:04:18,830 --> 01:04:21,290
...that our children's hearts beat,
每一次心跳...

859
01:04:21,310 --> 01:04:23,780
that they draw breath,
每一次呼吸...

860
01:04:23,950 --> 01:04:27,580
that they walk and speak and...
他们的行走 说话...

861
01:04:30,290 --> 01:04:33,920
...smile, argue, play.
欢笑 吵闹和嬉戏当作理所当然的

862
01:04:36,360 --> 01:04:40,340
Never forget for a moment that they may be gone.
得时刻提醒自己 他们可能说没就没了

863
01:04:47,420 --> 01:04:49,320
Jude.
妹妹

864
01:05:31,680 --> 01:05:32,970
Jude.
小珠

865
01:05:44,600 --> 01:05:46,470
Don't be sad.
别难过

866
01:05:48,740 --> 01:05:51,040
You shall be well.
你要替我好好活下去

867
01:05:51,800 --> 01:05:53,740
I shall not.
我不能

868
01:05:54,190 --> 01:05:56,370
Not without you.
没有你我活不下去

869
01:06:08,520 --> 01:06:10,130
It's here.
它来了

870
01:06:10,140 --> 01:06:11,870
Do you see it, Jude?
妹妹 你看得到吗？

871
01:06:18,430 --> 01:06:20,300
It's watching us.
它在看着咱们呢

872
01:06:21,750 --> 01:06:24,100
I'll tell it to take us both.
我要告诉它把咱们都带走

873
01:06:24,110 --> 01:06:25,930
We'll go together.
要走一起走

874
01:06:33,690 --> 01:06:35,590
Turn away.
转过去

875
01:06:36,080 --> 01:06:37,920
Turn away.
转过去

876
01:06:45,220 --> 01:06:47,140
It'll make a mistake.
它会看错的

877
01:06:48,420 --> 01:06:50,530
It can't tell us apart.
它分不出咱俩谁是谁

878
01:06:53,040 --> 01:06:55,250
Breathe with me, Judith.
跟我一起呼吸 珠迪丝

879
01:07:27,200 --> 01:07:30,040
I give you my life.
我把我的命给你

880
01:07:30,190 --> 01:07:32,420
You shall be well.
你会活下去的

881
01:07:32,550 --> 01:07:35,450
I give you my life, Judith.
用我的命换你的 珠迪丝

882
01:07:41,680 --> 01:07:43,750
I'll be brave.
我很勇敢

883
01:07:45,330 --> 01:07:47,790
I'll be brave, Father.
我是个男子汉 爹

884
01:07:47,810 --> 01:07:49,610
I'll be brave.
我很勇敢

885
01:07:52,300 --> 01:07:54,050
I'll be brave.
我很勇敢

886
01:07:55,740 --> 01:07:57,480
I'll be brave, Father.
我是个男子汉 爹

887
01:07:57,490 --> 01:07:59,160
I'll be brave.
我是个男子汉

888
01:08:01,660 --> 01:08:03,670
I'll be brave.
我很勇敢

889
01:08:30,630 --> 01:08:31,630
Whoa.
驭

890
01:08:33,760 --> 01:08:35,390
Quick as you can.
赶快

891
01:09:21,160 --> 01:09:22,810
Hamnet.
哈姆奈特

892
01:09:22,830 --> 01:09:24,190
Hamnet, you're not supposed to be down here.
醒醒 你不该在这儿睡

893
01:09:24,200 --> 01:09:25,910
I need to take you up to bed.
来 我抱你上楼睡觉去...

894
01:09:32,130 --> 01:09:33,570
Hamnet.
哈姆奈特

895
01:09:35,290 --> 01:09:36,890
Hamnet?
哥哥？

896
01:09:57,910 --> 01:09:59,550
Mama.
娘

897
01:10:02,690 --> 01:10:04,290
Mama.
娘

898
01:10:07,380 --> 01:10:08,950
Mama.
娘啊

899
01:10:56,690 --> 01:10:58,450
Hamnet.
哈姆奈特

900
01:10:58,680 --> 01:11:00,480
You must open your mouth.
你得张开嘴

901
01:11:01,830 --> 01:11:03,150
All will be well.
会没事的

902
01:11:13,850 --> 01:11:15,450
He's burning.
他在发烧

903
01:11:15,590 --> 01:11:16,990
He's burning up.
烧得太高了

904
01:11:17,010 --> 01:11:19,090
It will not sti-- It will not stick!
药不起作用 不起作用

905
01:11:21,200 --> 01:11:22,500
A stone. There's a stone.
拿石头 拿石头

906
01:11:21,200 --> 01:11:26,350
{\an8}【有洞的石头: 当时民间信仰认为病气能从一孔进 一孔出】

907
01:11:22,510 --> 01:11:24,300
There's a stone upstairs with a hole in the middle of it.
楼上有块中间有洞的石头

908
01:11:24,320 --> 01:11:26,340
By his bedside. Bring it down. I need it.
在他床边 快去拿来 快去

909
01:11:26,350 --> 01:11:28,500
And, um, uh, salt. Get salt.
还要盐 拿盐 得撒盐

910
01:11:26,350 --> 01:11:32,690
{\an8}【撒盐: 当时认为能建立保护屏障 驱挡邪灵和病气】

911
01:11:28,510 --> 01:11:29,780
Get it. Can you give it?
能去拿吗？

912
01:11:29,800 --> 01:11:32,430
Can you f-fetch me some salt, as much salt as you have.
多拿点盐 有多少拿多少

913
01:11:32,690 --> 01:11:34,360
Water. We need water.
水 还要水

914
01:11:34,370 --> 01:11:36,300
He's... he's too hot.
他 他烧得太厉害了

915
01:11:36,310 --> 01:11:37,830
He's burning.
太厉害了

916
01:11:37,840 --> 01:11:39,880
My love. Mama's here.
我的孩子 娘在这儿

917
01:11:39,900 --> 01:11:41,790
All will be well. All will be well.
坚持住 都会好的

918
01:11:41,850 --> 01:11:43,510
All will be well.
都会好的

919
01:11:46,860 --> 01:11:48,570
All will be well.
都会好的

920
01:11:52,230 --> 01:11:55,520
Hamnet, don't be scared.
哈姆奈特 别怕

921
01:11:55,540 --> 01:11:57,130
No need to be scared.
没什么好怕的

922
01:11:57,150 --> 01:11:59,110
All will be well. Mommy's here.
都会没事的 娘在这儿

923
01:11:59,130 --> 01:12:01,760
Mommy's here. It's okay.
娘在 没事的

924
01:12:01,810 --> 01:12:03,200
Mommy's here.
娘在这儿

925
01:12:03,220 --> 01:12:05,000
Look at me. Mommy's here.
你看 娘在这儿

926
01:12:05,010 --> 01:12:07,840
I will never, ever let you go.
我绝不 绝不会放手的

927
01:12:08,300 --> 01:12:09,170
You understand?
明白吗？

928
01:12:09,190 --> 01:12:11,980
I will never, ever let you go.
娘绝不 绝不会放手的

929
01:12:11,990 --> 01:12:13,590
I love you.
娘的心肝啊

930
01:12:15,510 --> 01:12:16,810
I love you.
心肝啊

931
01:12:26,400 --> 01:12:29,600
Eliza, take Judith to the kitchen and keep her there.
伊莱莎 把珠迪丝抱到厨房去

932
01:12:29,610 --> 01:12:30,980
Please!
我不走

933
01:12:32,940 --> 01:12:35,200
- He needs me! - Stay there.
- 我得陪他 - 带她走

934
01:12:35,240 --> 01:12:37,570
He needs me!
我要陪我哥

935
01:12:37,630 --> 01:12:39,060
Please!
我不走

936
01:12:44,370 --> 01:12:46,060
Valerian...
缬草啊...

937
01:12:47,600 --> 01:12:50,380
Hamnet. Hamnet. Hamnet.
哈姆奈特 哈姆奈特 哈姆奈特

938
01:12:50,390 --> 01:12:53,090
Hamnet, you have to stay. Hamnet, please.
坚持住 坚持住 求你了

939
01:12:53,290 --> 01:12:55,290
Hamnet, please. You have to stay with us.
哈姆奈特 求你了 你要坚持住 别离开我们

940
01:12:55,300 --> 01:12:56,880
Mama needs you. We need you.
娘需要你 我们都需要你

941
01:12:56,900 --> 01:12:59,090
- Stop! Enough! - Stay with us. Stay, stay.
- 住手 够了 - 别离开我们 坚持住 坚持

942
01:12:59,100 --> 01:13:00,520
Please, Hamnet. Hamnet, Hamnet, Hamnet.
求求你了 哈姆奈特 坚持住 坚持住

943
01:13:00,530 --> 01:13:01,880
- Let him alone! - Hamnet, please!
- 别折腾他了 - 求求你了 哈姆奈特

944
01:13:01,890 --> 01:13:04,990
Can't you see that it's too late for him!
你看不出来吗 太晚了

945
01:13:06,040 --> 01:13:08,340
Please, please.
求你了 求你了

946
01:13:08,390 --> 01:13:09,650
Hamnet?
哈姆奈特？

947
01:13:09,820 --> 01:13:12,120
Hamnet. Hamnet. Please. Hamnet.
哈姆奈特 哈姆奈特 求你了 哈姆奈特

948
01:13:57,350 --> 01:13:59,650
My son is gone.
我儿子没了

949
01:14:00,770 --> 01:14:03,250
Just so bereft... it's my son.
没了 我的儿子

950
01:14:03,430 --> 01:14:05,060
I've lost my...
没了 我...

951
01:15:12,820 --> 01:15:15,030
I saw the light, and I couldn't sleep.
我看灯还亮着 我也睡不着

952
01:15:23,490 --> 01:15:25,200
Here.
来

953
01:15:45,140 --> 01:15:46,700
Oh, child, no.
哎呀 孩子 不行

954
01:15:46,720 --> 01:15:49,440
- No, no, no. Go to bed. - No, no, let-let her stay.
- 不 快去睡觉 - 没事 没事 让她看吧

955
01:15:53,080 --> 01:15:55,260
It is my fault, Mama. It is my fault.
是我害的 娘 都是我害的

956
01:15:55,280 --> 01:15:57,450
No. No.
不 不

957
01:15:58,200 --> 01:16:02,140
It is not your fault, Judith.
珠迪丝 这不是你的错

958
01:16:02,160 --> 01:16:04,170
But he changed places with me.
他替了我

959
01:16:04,350 --> 01:16:05,740
He tricked it.
他骗了它

960
01:16:05,750 --> 01:16:07,200
He tricked what?
他骗了什么？

961
01:16:07,210 --> 01:16:08,440
Death.
死神

962
01:16:08,830 --> 01:16:09,920
Judith.
珠迪丝

963
01:16:09,940 --> 01:16:12,440
It took him when it came for me.
它来找我时 却把他夺走了

964
01:16:13,440 --> 01:16:16,180
Never say those words to anyone ever again.
这话绝对不许再说

965
01:16:17,930 --> 01:16:20,830
The fever came for your brother, and it took him.
你哥是因为发烧走的

966
01:16:21,880 --> 01:16:24,110
Do you wish to see him?
你想看看他吗？

967
01:16:25,380 --> 01:16:26,750
Yes.
想

968
01:16:35,390 --> 01:16:37,390
Go on. You can see him.
去吧 去看看他

969
01:16:49,270 --> 01:16:51,240
Is it really him?
这真的是他吗？

970
01:16:52,770 --> 01:16:54,170
Yes.
是的

971
01:16:56,790 --> 01:16:59,720
It-it doesn't look like him.
这 这不像我哥

972
01:17:02,590 --> 01:17:03,930
No.
不

973
01:17:10,590 --> 01:17:12,720
It's not him.
这不是他

974
01:17:13,250 --> 01:17:14,820
It's not.
不是

975
01:17:16,060 --> 01:17:17,310
It's not him.
这不是我哥

976
01:17:19,780 --> 01:17:21,490
It-It's-it's not morning yet.
天 天还没亮呢

977
01:17:21,510 --> 01:17:23,440
We haven't prepared him properly.
还没给他收拾好呢

978
01:17:25,190 --> 01:17:27,120
Am I too late?
我来晚了吗？

979
01:17:33,300 --> 01:17:34,430
- It's you. - Father.
- 是你 - 爹

980
01:17:34,450 --> 01:17:35,690
It's you.
真的是你

981
01:17:42,700 --> 01:17:44,030
It's me.
真是我

982
01:18:02,010 --> 01:18:03,640
Where is he?
儿子呢？

983
01:18:06,520 --> 01:18:08,020
Where is...
他在哪儿...

984
01:18:12,530 --> 01:18:13,900
Where...
他在...

985
01:18:58,840 --> 01:19:01,130
It's my boy.
是我儿子

986
01:19:05,430 --> 01:19:07,400
It's my boy.
是我的儿子啊

987
01:19:29,180 --> 01:19:31,150
I didn't see it.
我没预见到

988
01:19:38,190 --> 01:19:40,500
I should've paid him more attention.
我该多留心哈姆奈特的

989
01:19:40,520 --> 01:19:42,620
I always thought she was the one to be taken away
我一直以为会失去珠迪丝

990
01:19:42,640 --> 01:19:44,970
when all the while it was him.
没想到是儿子

991
01:19:46,060 --> 01:19:47,050
I'm a fool.
我太蠢了

992
01:19:47,070 --> 01:19:49,940
No, there's nothing anyone could have done to save him.
不是 没人能救他

993
01:19:50,960 --> 01:19:52,690
You did everything that you could.
你已经尽力了

994
01:19:52,700 --> 01:19:54,440
Of course I did.
我是尽力了

995
01:19:56,170 --> 01:19:57,790
You weren't here.
可你人呢？

996
01:19:57,810 --> 01:19:59,580
I would have cut my heart out and given it to him.
我愿把心掏给他

997
01:19:59,600 --> 01:20:01,430
I would have laid my life down on the ground for him.
用我的命换他的命

998
01:20:01,450 --> 01:20:03,340
- I-I know. I know. - And no one would take it.
- 我懂 我懂 - 可上天不收

999
01:20:03,360 --> 01:20:05,950
- But you... - No, you don't know.
- 可你... - 不 你不懂

1000
01:20:06,130 --> 01:20:08,830
You don't know. You weren't here.
你怎么可能懂 你都不在啊

1001
01:20:10,560 --> 01:20:12,200
He died in agony.
他在折磨中死去

1002
01:20:12,220 --> 01:20:13,590
I...
我...

1003
01:20:16,590 --> 01:20:18,510
- He was in agony. - Agnes.
- 受尽了折磨 - 安妮丝

1004
01:20:18,530 --> 01:20:20,060
He cried and he cried
他哭个不停 他哭啊 哭啊

1005
01:20:20,070 --> 01:20:21,730
- and he cried and he cried. - Agnes, stop, stop.
-  哭啊 哭啊 哭啊 - 安妮丝 别这样

1006
01:20:21,750 --> 01:20:23,330
- And his little body was wracked in pain. - Shh.
- 他小小的身子在剧痛中抽搐 - 嘘

1007
01:20:23,340 --> 01:20:24,590
No, don't shush me.
不 别让我闭嘴

1008
01:20:24,600 --> 01:20:25,980
He was so scared.
他当时好害怕

1009
01:20:26,000 --> 01:20:27,820
- And you weren't here. - I know.
- 你却没在身边 - 我知道

1010
01:20:31,990 --> 01:20:33,810
I tried everything I could.
我什么办法都用了

1011
01:20:33,820 --> 01:20:35,410
I know you did.
我知道你做了

1012
01:20:35,550 --> 01:20:38,250
- I tried everything I could. - You did everything that you could.
- 我什么都试过了 - 你已经尽了一切

1013
01:20:38,260 --> 01:20:40,980
You did everything that you could.
你已经用尽了一切办法

1014
01:20:41,000 --> 01:20:42,560
Everything.
一切办法

1015
01:20:44,120 --> 01:20:46,540
Everything.
一切办法

1016
01:20:48,600 --> 01:20:51,110
Agnes. Agnes.
安妮丝 安妮丝

1017
01:21:14,480 --> 01:21:16,440
I will send word, Agnes.
我会捎信的 安妮丝

1018
01:21:16,460 --> 01:21:18,700
You'll send word?
捎信？

1019
01:21:19,020 --> 01:21:21,250
- To whom? - To you.
- 捎给谁啊？ - 给你啊

1020
01:21:28,860 --> 01:21:30,820
I'm here.
我就在这儿啊

1021
01:21:31,980 --> 01:21:34,540
What I meant was that I shall send word when I reach London.
我是说到了伦敦我会给你捎信的

1022
01:21:34,550 --> 01:21:36,180
London?
伦敦？

1023
01:21:37,710 --> 01:21:39,510
I must leave.
我得走了

1024
01:21:42,810 --> 01:21:44,590
Leave? How can you leave?
走？你怎么能走？

1025
01:21:44,600 --> 01:21:47,940
The world does simply not stand still, Agnes.
世界不会因为我们就停下来 安妮丝

1026
01:21:51,020 --> 01:21:53,010
There are people waiting for me in London.
伦敦还有人在等我

1027
01:21:53,410 --> 01:21:54,760
The season is about to begin,
演出季马上就要开始了

1028
01:21:54,770 --> 01:21:57,860
and my company shall return from Kent any day now.
我们的剧团随时都会从肯特郡回来

1029
01:22:03,560 --> 01:22:06,110
I have to go now.
我现在就得走了

1030
01:22:06,120 --> 01:22:07,690
Now?
现在？

1031
01:22:08,310 --> 01:22:10,000
There's a traveling party leaving today,
今天有个商队要出发

1032
01:22:10,010 --> 01:22:12,810
and they have a spare horse, so yeah.
他们有匹多余的马 现在就得走

1033
01:22:14,640 --> 01:22:16,620
Look after the girls, and I will return to--
照看好女儿们 我回来时会...

1034
01:22:16,640 --> 01:22:18,000
Stop.
住手

1035
01:22:18,770 --> 01:22:20,990
Don't.
别碰我

1036
01:22:48,540 --> 01:22:50,660
Go. Go.
走吧 你走吧

1037
01:23:00,340 --> 01:23:10,300
{\an8}（哈姆奈特）

1038
01:23:02,840 --> 01:23:06,490
"When I do count the clock that tells the time,
“蒙晨暮鼓催岁长”

1039
01:23:06,510 --> 01:23:10,370
"And see the brave day sunk in hideous night;
“夕太沉沉入幽光”

1040
01:23:10,390 --> 01:23:13,860
"When I behold the violet past prime,
“芳草奇花香自散”

1041
01:23:13,870 --> 01:23:17,930
"And sable curls all silver'd o'er with white;
“青丝墨字今已霜”

1042
01:23:17,940 --> 01:23:22,020
"When lofty trees I see barren of leaves
“繁荫不复幕沧桑”

1043
01:23:22,030 --> 01:23:25,830
"Which erst from the heat did canopy the herd,
“牧群归舍众组忙”

1044
01:23:25,840 --> 01:23:29,960
"And summer's green all girded up in sheaves
“夏末青禾束成囊”

1045
01:23:29,970 --> 01:23:34,840
"Borne on the bier with white and bristly beard;
“犹似亡魂缠白裳”

1046
01:23:34,860 --> 01:23:38,350
"Then of thy beauty do I question make,
“容颜岂非浮云妆”

1047
01:23:38,360 --> 01:23:41,330
"Thou among the wastes of time must go,
“终将消散入苍茫”

1048
01:23:41,340 --> 01:23:45,140
"Since sweets and beauties do themselves forsake
“芬芳娇艳随风扬”

1049
01:23:45,150 --> 01:23:48,420
"And die as fast as they see others grow;
“新生如笋催人苍”

1050
01:23:48,430 --> 01:23:51,530
"And nothing gainst time's scythe can make defense
“时光镰刀谁能挡”

1051
01:23:51,540 --> 01:23:55,900
Save breed, to brave him when he takes thee hence."
“勇敢生育续春阳”

1052
01:23:51,540 --> 01:23:56,970
{\an8}【十四行诗: 现代编号第12首 以时间流逝与生育为主题】

1053
01:23:56,970 --> 01:23:58,980
Will you read it again?
能再读一遍吗？

1054
01:23:59,320 --> 01:24:00,890
No.
不了

1055
01:24:00,950 --> 01:24:02,960
I've read it three times.
我已经读了三遍了

1056
01:24:04,010 --> 01:24:05,760
That's enough.
行了

1057
01:24:09,010 --> 01:24:11,600
- Shall we do presents? - Presents? from London?
- 咱们开始拆礼物吧 - 什么礼物？伦敦的吗？

1058
01:24:11,620 --> 01:24:13,630
A hair comb for you, Jude.
给你的梳子 小珠

1059
01:24:15,840 --> 01:24:17,870
Mind you, you'll have to be careful.
爱惜点用 别弄坏了

1060
01:24:24,280 --> 01:24:26,000
This is for you, Agnes.
这是给你的 安妮丝

1061
01:24:35,360 --> 01:24:38,010
- A ruby, is it? - Mm-hmm.
- 红宝石吗？ - 是的

1062
01:24:38,030 --> 01:24:40,720
It's the finest I've ever seen.
从没见过这么漂亮的

1063
01:24:41,280 --> 01:24:43,810
Everyone's talking about the new house.
大家都在议论那栋新房子

1064
01:24:43,830 --> 01:24:45,670
It's the biggest in Stratford.
那是斯特拉特福镇上最大的房子

1065
01:24:45,680 --> 01:24:48,560
There are so many rooms. One could get lost.
房间多到人进去都能走丢

1066
01:24:48,570 --> 01:24:50,930
You shall keep the keys, Susanna.
苏珊娜 那就好好照看好

1067
01:24:50,950 --> 01:24:53,150
You shall manage the house well.
打理好咱们的房子

1068
01:24:54,860 --> 01:24:56,500
Put it on, Mama.
娘 你戴上试试

1069
01:25:16,410 --> 01:25:19,700
Did Bartholomew show you the new house?
你哥巴塞洛缪带你看过那栋房子了吗？

1070
01:25:19,710 --> 01:25:21,140
Mm-hmm.
看了

1071
01:25:23,270 --> 01:25:24,970
Do you like it?
你喜欢吗？

1072
01:25:26,530 --> 01:25:28,760
Why didn't you show me yourself?
你怎么不亲自带我去看的？

1073
01:25:30,380 --> 01:25:32,920
Were you afraid I wouldn't leave?
是怕我不愿离开吗？

1074
01:25:34,650 --> 01:25:37,180
'Cause Hamnet died here in this house.
因为哈姆奈特死在这个房子里

1075
01:25:46,130 --> 01:25:48,670
You know, I'm constantly wondering where he is.
我一直在想他在哪儿？

1076
01:25:50,380 --> 01:25:52,390
Or where he has gone.
他去了哪儿？

1077
01:25:55,020 --> 01:25:58,850
Whatever I'm doing, I'm wondering, "Where is he?"
不管我做什么 脑子里都是他在哪儿？

1078
01:25:59,730 --> 01:26:02,060
I mean, he can't have just vanished.
他不能就这么凭空没了啊

1079
01:26:04,760 --> 01:26:06,760
All he needs is for me to find him.
我一定要找到他

1080
01:26:06,780 --> 01:26:09,250
He must be somewhere.
他肯定在哪个地方

1081
01:26:10,360 --> 01:26:14,230
I fear I may run mad with it, even now, a year on.
都一年了还是这样 我真害怕自己会疯掉

1082
01:26:14,350 --> 01:26:16,250
A year is nothing.
一年算什么啊

1083
01:26:20,460 --> 01:26:24,320
A year is nothing. It's every second...
一年什么都不是 每时每刻...

1084
01:26:24,420 --> 01:26:26,590
every minute, every day.
每分每秒 每天每年

1085
01:26:29,040 --> 01:26:32,270
We may never stop looking for him.
我们怎么可能停止寻找啊

1086
01:26:33,770 --> 01:26:35,810
I'm sorry, Agnes.
对不起 安妮丝

1087
01:26:38,800 --> 01:26:40,200
Did you hear me? I said that I'm sorry, Agnes.
听到了吗？我说对不起 安妮丝

1088
01:26:40,210 --> 01:26:41,490
- For what? - For everything.
- 为什么道歉？ - 为这一切

1089
01:26:41,500 --> 01:26:43,000
- You're caught by that place. - For...
- 你被那地方缠住了 - 为...

1090
01:26:43,020 --> 01:26:44,930
- What place? - That place in your head.
- 什么地方？ - 你脑子里那个地方

1091
01:26:44,950 --> 01:26:46,610
It is now more real to you than anywhere else.
对你来说 那地方比什么都好

1092
01:26:46,620 --> 01:26:50,510
Not even the death of our child can keep you from it.
连咱儿子死了都留不住你

1093
01:26:51,970 --> 01:26:54,100
Hamnet died.
哈姆奈特死了

1094
01:26:54,290 --> 01:26:56,090
A horrible death.
死得很惨

1095
01:26:57,460 --> 01:26:59,630
And you should have been there.
你本该在场

1096
01:27:00,780 --> 01:27:02,820
You could have bid him farewell.
你本可跟他道个别

1097
01:27:32,670 --> 01:27:34,710
What do you see?
你看到了什么？

1098
01:27:36,050 --> 01:27:37,490
Hmm?
什么？

1099
01:27:41,950 --> 01:27:43,520
Nothing.
什么都没有

1100
01:27:48,220 --> 01:27:49,820
Nothing?
什么都没有？

1101
01:27:51,980 --> 01:27:53,850
Nothing at all.
什么都没有

1102
01:27:53,950 --> 01:27:55,630
Oh, well.
好吧

1103
01:28:00,380 --> 01:28:02,680
You should go back to London.
你还是回伦敦吧

1104
01:28:04,740 --> 01:28:08,070
You need not concern yourself with us.
不用为我们操心

1105
01:28:09,370 --> 01:28:12,240
Get along just fine without you.
没有你我们的日子也照过

1106
01:28:15,190 --> 01:28:17,370
This was sometime a paradox,
“这句话从前是个似是而非的悖论”

1107
01:28:17,380 --> 01:28:20,320
but now the time gives it proof.
“如今已被时间所证实”

1108
01:28:20,670 --> 01:28:22,480
I did love you once.
“我确实曾爱过你”

1109
01:28:22,500 --> 01:28:26,300
Indeed, my lord, you made me believe so.
“没错 殿下 您确实让我信以为真”

1110
01:28:26,340 --> 01:28:29,530
You should not have believed me,
“你当初就不该相信我”

1111
01:28:29,690 --> 01:28:34,530
for virtue cannot so inoculate our old stock for...
“美德嫁接到我们这罪恶的老树干上 也...”

1112
01:28:36,150 --> 01:28:38,020
You should not have believed me,
“你当初就不该相信我”

1113
01:28:38,040 --> 01:28:40,870
for virtue cannot so inoculate our old stock
“美德嫁接到我们这罪恶的老树干上”

1114
01:28:40,890 --> 01:28:42,990
but we shall relish of it.
“也结不出好果”

1115
01:28:44,770 --> 01:28:46,610
I loved you not.
“我从未真爱过你”

1116
01:28:47,660 --> 01:28:50,070
I was the more deceived.
“那我真是被深深欺骗了”

1117
01:28:51,380 --> 01:28:53,760
Get thee to a nunnery.
“去美人庵吧”

1118
01:28:51,380 --> 01:28:57,220
{\an8}【美人庵: 指女性宗教修行场所 又为妓院俚语 此处含贬低之意】

1119
01:28:53,990 --> 01:28:57,190
Why wouldst thou be a breeder of sinners?
“干嘛非得生出一堆罪人来？”

1120
01:28:57,220 --> 01:28:59,630
I am myself indifferent honest,
“我自己还算个老实人”

1121
01:28:59,650 --> 01:29:01,770
but yet I could accuse me of such things
“但我的罪过却多得数不清”

1122
01:29:01,790 --> 01:29:03,770
that it were better to...
“最大的莫过于...”

1123
01:29:03,790 --> 01:29:05,650
Again.
重来

1124
01:29:06,360 --> 01:29:08,350
Get thee to a nunnery.
“去美人庵吧”

1125
01:29:09,450 --> 01:29:12,300
Why wouldst thou be a breeder of sinners?
“干嘛非得生出一堆罪人来？”

1126
01:29:12,310 --> 01:29:14,720
I am myself indifferent honest, but...
“我自己也算个老实人 但...”

1127
01:29:14,730 --> 01:29:16,760
Again. "I am myself indifferent honest." Again.
重来 是“我自己还算个老实人” 重来

1128
01:29:16,770 --> 01:29:18,790
I am myself indifferent honest,
“我自己还算个老实人”

1129
01:29:18,800 --> 01:29:21,240
but yet I could accuse me of such things that it were better
“但我的罪过却多得数不清 最大的莫过于”

1130
01:29:21,260 --> 01:29:23,780
- my mother had not borne me. - Again.
- “我娘把我生了出来” - 重来

1131
01:29:24,980 --> 01:29:27,450
I, myself...
“我这个人...”

1132
01:29:27,630 --> 01:29:29,510
- And... - Again.
- 呃... - 再来

1133
01:29:29,530 --> 01:29:31,190
I, myself, am indifferent...
“我这个人...自己还算个...”

1134
01:29:31,210 --> 01:29:32,840
"I am myself."
是“我自己”

1135
01:29:32,850 --> 01:29:35,820
I am myself indifferent honest,
“我自己还算个老实人”

1136
01:29:35,930 --> 01:29:39,080
but yet I could accuse me of such things that it were...
“但我的罪过却多得数不清...”

1137
01:29:39,100 --> 01:29:40,420
Again.
再来

1138
01:29:40,430 --> 01:29:42,040
But yet I could accuse me of such things that it were...
“但我的罪过却多得数不清...”

1139
01:29:42,050 --> 01:29:43,220
Again!
重来

1140
01:29:43,470 --> 01:29:45,050
I am myself indifferent honest,
“我自己还算个老实人”

1141
01:29:45,070 --> 01:29:46,050
but yet I could accuse me of such...
“但我的罪过...”

1142
01:29:46,060 --> 01:29:48,660
You are simply mouthing the words!
你根本没投入

1143
01:29:51,510 --> 01:29:54,620
I am myself indifferent honest,
我自己还算个老实人

1144
01:29:54,780 --> 01:29:57,060
but yet I could accuse me of such things
但我的罪过却多得数不清

1145
01:29:57,070 --> 01:30:00,230
that it were better my mother had not borne me.
最大的莫过于我娘把我生了出来

1146
01:30:01,650 --> 01:30:04,810
I am very proud, revengeful, ambitious,
我这人自傲 报复心强 野心大

1147
01:30:04,820 --> 01:30:06,510
with more offenses at my beck
肚子里装的那些坏主意

1148
01:30:06,520 --> 01:30:08,870
than I have thoughts to put them in,
多到我都数不清

1149
01:30:10,230 --> 01:30:14,630
imagination to give them shape or time to act them in.
想都想不尽 干也干不完

1150
01:30:15,330 --> 01:30:17,000
Now, what should such fellows as I do
像我这样的人

1151
01:30:17,020 --> 01:30:18,840
crawling between heaven and earth?
在天地之间苟活 有什么用？

1152
01:30:18,850 --> 01:30:20,220
We are arrant knaves all.
我们全是烂透的坏人

1153
01:30:20,240 --> 01:30:22,930
Believe none of us.
你可千万不要信我们

1154
01:30:22,960 --> 01:30:25,690
Go thy ways to a nunnery. Again.
去你的美人庵吧 重来

1155
01:31:09,670 --> 01:31:11,010
To be...
生存...

1156
01:31:16,260 --> 01:31:18,230
...or not to be...
还是毁灭...

1157
01:31:25,910 --> 01:31:27,940
...that is the question:
这是个问题

1158
01:31:35,580 --> 01:31:40,190
Whether 'tis nobler in the mind to... suffer
哪种更高贵？是默然 忍受...

1159
01:31:40,300 --> 01:31:42,930
The slings and arrows of...
命运投来的巨石...

1160
01:31:45,730 --> 01:31:48,000
...outrageous fortune...
射来的毒箭？

1161
01:31:51,250 --> 01:31:52,880
...Or...
还是...

1162
01:31:55,040 --> 01:31:57,570
...to take arms against a...
挺身反抗...

1163
01:31:59,760 --> 01:32:02,080
...sea of troubles,
汹涌的苦海...

1164
01:32:02,100 --> 01:32:04,500
And by opposing...
通过斗争...

1165
01:32:06,300 --> 01:32:07,860
...end them.
渡向彼岸？

1166
01:33:09,950 --> 01:33:13,150
♪ I pray that those trees ♪
♪ 我祈求那些树啊 ♪

1167
01:33:13,170 --> 01:33:16,320
♪ Will return my boy ♪
♪ 还我男孩来 ♪

1168
01:33:16,340 --> 01:33:18,570
♪ For ♪
♪ 只因... ♪

1169
01:33:18,590 --> 01:33:21,840
♪ Sweet bonny Robin ♪
♪ 那只温柔的知更鸟 ♪

1170
01:33:21,850 --> 01:33:25,510
♪ Is all my joy. ♪
♪ 是我仅有的幸福 ♪

1171
01:33:21,850 --> 01:33:28,760
{\an8}【《我那去了绿林的知更鸟》: 英国民谣 绿林象征身后世界 知更鸟象征逝者】

1172
01:33:33,280 --> 01:33:35,150
Agnes?
安妮丝？

1173
01:33:36,680 --> 01:33:38,640
I... I was in town, and I...
我 我碰巧来镇上

1174
01:33:38,770 --> 01:33:41,010
I thought I would pay you a visit.
就想顺路来看下你

1175
01:33:42,380 --> 01:33:45,970
I was very sorry to hear about John's passing.
听说你公公约翰去世了 替你们难过

1176
01:33:46,460 --> 01:33:48,210
How's your husband?
你丈夫还好吧

1177
01:33:48,230 --> 01:33:50,230
It's a... it's a terrible thing to lose one's father.
失去父亲 真是件悲痛的事啊

1178
01:33:50,240 --> 01:33:51,810
He's well.
他好得很

1179
01:33:51,830 --> 01:33:54,120
He's very busy. He's preparing a comedy.
忙得要命 还在搞一出喜剧

1180
01:33:54,580 --> 01:33:57,350
His new play is not a comedy.
他的新剧可不是喜剧

1181
01:33:58,350 --> 01:34:00,380
It's a tragedy.
是悲剧

1182
01:34:00,520 --> 01:34:02,860
But you knew that.
你应该早知道了

1183
01:34:03,020 --> 01:34:05,780
Everyone in town is talking about it.
镇上人人都在谈论

1184
01:34:15,880 --> 01:34:18,060
I did warn you about marrying him...
我是劝过你别嫁给他...

1185
01:34:18,130 --> 01:34:20,460
Don't pretend that you care for me.
别装作疼我

1186
01:34:22,230 --> 01:34:25,790
You are not my mother, and you never were.
你不是我娘 永远也不是

1187
01:34:35,940 --> 01:34:37,800
Good day, Agnes.
再见 安妮丝

1188
01:34:43,000 --> 01:34:44,400
He's not spoken to us for months.
他都好几个月没跟我们联系了

1189
01:34:44,410 --> 01:34:45,770
How could he...
他怎么能

1190
01:34:45,790 --> 01:34:47,440
How could he not tell us?
他怎么能不告诉我们呢？

1191
01:34:47,650 --> 01:34:50,220
Do you not wonder what is in it?
你不想看看吗？

1192
01:34:51,430 --> 01:34:53,290
In what?
看什么？

1193
01:34:53,310 --> 01:34:56,680
{\an8}（《哈姆雷特的悲剧》）

1194
01:34:53,710 --> 01:34:55,390
The play.
这剧

1195
01:36:10,100 --> 01:36:12,130
Who are you looking for?
你们找谁呢？

1196
01:36:12,480 --> 01:36:14,970
William Shakespeare.
威廉·莎士比亚

1197
01:36:14,980 --> 01:36:16,850
We're his family from Stratford.
我们是他的家人 从斯特拉特福来的

1198
01:36:16,860 --> 01:36:19,390
Go up the stairs. He lives in the attic.
上楼 他住阁楼

1199
01:36:36,140 --> 01:36:38,440
Why would the man with the largest house in Stratford
拥有斯特拉特福最大房子的人

1200
01:36:38,460 --> 01:36:40,570
be living here?
怎么会住在这样的地方？

1201
01:36:51,970 --> 01:36:53,780
I don't understand.
我不明白

1202
01:36:55,370 --> 01:36:57,000
I thought...
我以为...

1203
01:36:58,340 --> 01:36:59,870
I thought he...
我以为他...

1204
01:37:06,700 --> 01:37:08,840
What shall I do?
我该怎么办？

1205
01:37:11,790 --> 01:37:13,520
Keep your heart open.
敞开心扉

1206
01:37:19,600 --> 01:37:24,660
{\an2}（天下皆为舞台）

1207
01:37:19,600 --> 01:37:24,660
{\an8}【拉丁格言"天下皆为舞台 人人都是演员" 莎士比亚《皆大欢喜》亦用此意象】

1208
01:37:59,590 --> 01:38:02,780
{\an8}【译注: 当时剧场分为站票 看台 包厢等级】

1209
01:38:44,800 --> 01:38:46,900
{\an8}（《哈姆奈特的悲剧》）

1210
01:39:10,100 --> 01:39:12,740
- Who's there? - Nay, answer me:
- 谁呀？ - 不 先回答我

1211
01:39:12,760 --> 01:39:13,860
stand and unfold yourself!
出来 报上名来

1212
01:39:13,880 --> 01:39:15,400
Long live the king!
国王万岁

1213
01:39:13,880 --> 01:39:15,420
{\an8}【国王万岁: 执勤人员碰头暗号】

1214
01:39:15,430 --> 01:39:16,400
Bernardo?
伯纳多？

1215
01:39:16,420 --> 01:39:18,590
If you do meet Horatio and Marcellus,
要是碰到我的夜班同伴

1216
01:39:18,600 --> 01:39:21,860
The rivals to my watch, bid them make haste.
霍拉旭和马塞拉斯 叫他们速来

1217
01:39:21,880 --> 01:39:24,350
I think I hear them. Stand, ho!
他们好像来了 站住 谁

1218
01:39:24,750 --> 01:39:26,320
Who's there?
是谁？

1219
01:39:28,660 --> 01:39:30,870
Has this thing appeared again tonight?
它今晚又现身了吗？

1220
01:39:30,890 --> 01:39:32,700
- I have seen nothing. - Horatio says...
- 我还没看见 - 霍拉旭说...

1221
01:39:32,720 --> 01:39:34,430
What are they talking about?
这演的什么啊

1222
01:39:32,720 --> 01:39:34,430
{\an8}...'tis but our fantasy...
这不过是我们的幻觉

1223
01:39:34,450 --> 01:39:36,940
...and will not let belief take hold of him touching...
我曾和他说过 他就是不信...

1224
01:39:36,950 --> 01:39:39,980
What has any of this to do with my son?
这和我儿子有什么关系？

1225
01:39:36,950 --> 01:39:39,980
{\an8}...this dreaded sight twice seen of us...
我们已经见过两次这可怕的景象...

1226
01:39:39,990 --> 01:39:41,640
These men are frightened.
他们很害怕

1227
01:39:41,650 --> 01:39:43,140
Of what?
有什么好怕的

1228
01:39:42,540 --> 01:39:43,910
{\an8}And let us once again assail your ears...
别不信 让我们再给你解释一遍...

1229
01:39:43,920 --> 01:39:45,880
They watch for a ghost.
他们在提防一个幽灵

1230
01:39:46,070 --> 01:39:48,510
...when yond same star that's westward from the pole...
昨天这个时候 北极星西侧的星到这个位置时...

1231
01:39:48,780 --> 01:39:49,910
Ghost?
幽灵？

1232
01:39:49,920 --> 01:39:51,120
...The bell then beating one...
钟刚好敲了一下...

1233
01:39:51,140 --> 01:39:54,000
Peace; break thee off!
快住嘴 别说了

1234
01:39:54,330 --> 01:39:55,940
Look where it comes again!
看 它又现身了

1235
01:39:55,950 --> 01:39:59,050
In the same figure, like the king that's dead.
一模一样 就像那位已故的先王

1236
01:40:04,720 --> 01:40:06,400
See, it stalks away!
看 它阔步离去了

1237
01:40:06,420 --> 01:40:07,900
That was him.
那是他

1238
01:40:08,440 --> 01:40:09,560
...Tell me why this same...
谁能告诉我 为什么...

1239
01:40:09,570 --> 01:40:12,070
- That was Will. - Shh.
- 那是威廉 - 嘘

1240
01:40:12,250 --> 01:40:13,690
- He's not in the play. - No, no.
- 他不是演员 - 不 不

1241
01:40:13,700 --> 01:40:14,990
It was Will as a ghost.
那幽灵就是威廉演的

1242
01:40:15,000 --> 01:40:18,080
Our last king, Whose image but now appeared to us,
刚才向我们显灵的那位先王

1243
01:40:18,250 --> 01:40:21,790
Was dared to the combat; our valiant Hamlet...
正是那场决斗中 英勇的哈姆雷特国王...

1244
01:40:22,220 --> 01:40:24,180
Hamlet.
哈姆雷特

1245
01:40:24,550 --> 01:40:26,560
Did you hear... did you hear that?
你听到了 你听到了吗？

1246
01:40:26,570 --> 01:40:27,500
Yes.
听到了

1247
01:40:27,520 --> 01:40:29,430
They said his-- they said his name.
他们念了 念了他的名字

1248
01:40:29,450 --> 01:40:30,800
Agnes.
安妮丝

1249
01:40:30,880 --> 01:40:33,120
- Agnes, wait. - Out of my way!
- 安妮丝 别 - 让开

1250
01:40:33,220 --> 01:40:34,820
Please be quiet.
安静

1251
01:40:34,970 --> 01:40:37,440
Wait, did they say his name? Huh?
他们干嘛念他的名字啊

1252
01:40:37,450 --> 01:40:39,380
Do not upset yourself.
别自找苦吃

1253
01:40:39,620 --> 01:40:41,440
Why is-- Why did he use his name?
他凭什么 凭什么喊我儿子的名字？

1254
01:40:41,450 --> 01:40:43,070
- I don't know him. - Quiet.
- 他当他谁啊 - 安静

1255
01:40:43,080 --> 01:40:44,240
...and by my advice,
...依我之见

1256
01:40:44,260 --> 01:40:45,910
Let us impart what we have seen tonight
不如将我们今晚所见

1257
01:40:45,920 --> 01:40:47,120
Unto the young prince...
禀告给年轻的王子...

1258
01:40:47,140 --> 01:40:49,670
Don't you dare pronounce my son's name!
不许念我儿子的名字

1259
01:40:49,690 --> 01:40:50,850
Quiet!
闭嘴

1260
01:40:50,870 --> 01:40:53,500
...dumb to us, will speak to him.
...对我们沉默的幽灵 会对他说话

1261
01:41:00,430 --> 01:41:02,960
Though yet of our dear brother's death,
虽说大家对我亲爱的王兄死讯

1262
01:41:02,980 --> 01:41:04,420
The memory be green,
还记忆犹新

1263
01:41:04,430 --> 01:41:07,970
Yet so far hath discretion fought with nature
但我们要节哀顺变

1264
01:41:08,790 --> 01:41:11,980
That we with wisest sorrow think on him,
在深切缅怀他的同时

1265
01:41:12,040 --> 01:41:13,970
Together with remembrance of ourselves.
也要为我们自身着想啊

1266
01:41:13,990 --> 01:41:16,030
I will not stay a minute longer to be a part of this jest.
我受不了 我不能再看下去了

1267
01:41:16,050 --> 01:41:17,680
- Wait. One moment. - ...my cousin.
- 别急 再看一会儿 - 我的侄儿

1268
01:41:17,700 --> 01:41:19,640
- No. I want to go home. -  Hamlet...
- 不 我要回家 - 哈姆雷特

1269
01:41:17,700 --> 01:41:20,000
{\an8}【哈姆雷特: 原著中先王与王子同名皆为哈姆雷特】

1270
01:41:20,020 --> 01:41:21,970
and my son...
现在也是我的儿子

1271
01:41:25,580 --> 01:41:27,930
How is it that the clouds still hang on you?
你怎么还一脸愁云？

1272
01:41:27,940 --> 01:41:31,110
Good Hamlet, cast thy nighted color off.
我的好哈姆雷特 脱去这沉重的黑衣

1273
01:41:32,210 --> 01:41:34,820
Do not for ever with thy vailed lids
别总是低眉垂眼的

1274
01:41:34,830 --> 01:41:38,160
Seek for thy noble father in the dust.
仿佛要从尘土中寻出你高贵的父亲

1275
01:41:38,170 --> 01:41:40,830
All that lives must die,
万物有生必有死

1276
01:41:41,110 --> 01:41:44,180
Passing through nature to eternity.
顺其自然 谁都会踏入永恒

1277
01:41:44,320 --> 01:41:46,920
Ay, madam, it is common.
是啊 母后 这确实是常理

1278
01:41:47,940 --> 01:41:50,840
But I have that within which passes show.
但我心中的郁结

1279
01:41:50,850 --> 01:41:53,650
These are but the trappings and the suits of woe.
远非这些丧服哀装所能表达

1280
01:41:53,960 --> 01:41:56,660
To persevere In obstinate condolement
固执地沉溺于哀伤

1281
01:41:56,680 --> 01:41:59,750
is a course of impious stubbornness.
是一种逆天的愚行

1282
01:42:00,090 --> 01:42:02,590
'Tis unmanly grief.
这不是堂堂男子的悲伤

1283
01:42:02,770 --> 01:42:05,900
It shows a will most incorrect to heaven.
是对天意的违抗

1284
01:42:25,950 --> 01:42:27,630
Oh.
哦

1285
01:42:30,700 --> 01:42:35,800
This too, too solid flesh would melt,
真想这 这沉重的肉体消融

1286
01:42:35,940 --> 01:42:39,100
Thaw and resolve itself into a dew.
化为晨露消散

1287
01:42:39,910 --> 01:42:41,900
Or that the Everlasting had not fixed
真想永恒的真神

1288
01:42:41,910 --> 01:42:44,210
His canon gainst self-slaughter.
未曾禁止自杀这罪孽

1289
01:42:45,970 --> 01:42:48,880
'Tis an unweeded garden That grows to seed;
这就是一座荒芜不治 杂草丛生

1290
01:42:48,900 --> 01:42:52,670
things rank and gross in nature possess it merely.
长满毒花恶草的花园

1291
01:42:54,700 --> 01:42:57,270
That it should come to this.
谁曾料到啊

1292
01:42:59,190 --> 01:43:01,220
But two months dead--
才死了两个月

1293
01:43:01,430 --> 01:43:03,730
nay, not so much, not two--
不 还没满两个月

1294
01:43:04,040 --> 01:43:06,970
So excellent a king, that was to this
那是一位多么杰出的国王 如同太阳神

1295
01:43:07,040 --> 01:43:10,710
Hyperion to a... a satyr.
而现在这位 却像只肮脏的禽兽

1296
01:43:18,270 --> 01:43:20,270
Whither wilt thou lead me?
你要领我上哪儿去？

1297
01:43:20,290 --> 01:43:23,000
Speak. I'll go no further.
快说 我不跟你走

1298
01:43:24,020 --> 01:43:26,380
I am thy father's spirit,
我是你父亲的灵魂

1299
01:43:26,570 --> 01:43:29,180
Doomed for a certain term to walk the night,
被判在夜间游走于这大地

1300
01:43:29,190 --> 01:43:32,530
And for the day confined to fast in fires.
白天则要忍受地狱烈火的焚烧

1301
01:43:32,870 --> 01:43:34,630
My hour is almost come
我的时辰快到了

1302
01:43:34,640 --> 01:43:36,460
When I to sulfurous and tormenting flames
我又得回到硫磺的火焰中...

1303
01:43:36,480 --> 01:43:38,010
Must render up myself.
去遭受痛苦的煎熬

1304
01:43:38,020 --> 01:43:40,790
- Alas, poor ghost. - No, pity me not...
- 唉 可怜的幽灵 - 不 不要可怜我...

1305
01:43:42,450 --> 01:43:45,550
...but lend thy serious hearing to what I shall unfold.
你只要留心听着我要告诉你的话

1306
01:43:45,560 --> 01:43:47,160
List.
听好

1307
01:43:48,340 --> 01:43:49,720
List, oh, list.
听好 啊 听好了

1308
01:43:49,740 --> 01:43:52,280
If thou didst ever thy father love...
要是你曾深爱过你的父亲

1309
01:43:52,300 --> 01:43:53,080
Oh, God.
天呐

1310
01:43:53,100 --> 01:43:55,630
But soft, methinks I scent the morning air.
且慢 我仿佛闻到了清晨的气息

1311
01:43:56,150 --> 01:43:59,890
Brief let me be. Sleeping within my orchard.
我长话短说 那天我照常在花园里午睡

1312
01:43:59,910 --> 01:44:03,240
Upon my secure hour, thy uncle stole
你叔父趁我熟睡之际偷溜进来

1313
01:44:03,320 --> 01:44:05,480
With juice of cursed hebona in a vile,
拿着一瓶天杀的剧毒毒液

1314
01:44:05,490 --> 01:44:08,250
Within the porches of my ears did pour
灌入了我的耳朵

1315
01:44:08,260 --> 01:44:10,490
The leprous distillment...
这麻风病般的毒液...

1316
01:44:12,500 --> 01:44:16,360
...whose effect Holds such an enmity with blood of man
毒性之大 嗜血如仇

1317
01:44:16,370 --> 01:44:20,160
That swift as quicksilver it courses through
它顺着血管流动得比水银还快

1318
01:44:20,170 --> 01:44:24,010
The natural gates and alleys of the body.
流遍全身七窍八脉

1319
01:44:26,130 --> 01:44:28,270
And with a sudden vigor it doth posset
突然一下子

1320
01:44:28,280 --> 01:44:30,040
And curd, like...
就凝固了我的血...

1321
01:44:31,250 --> 01:44:32,980
...eager droppings into milk,
像卤水点豆腐一样

1322
01:44:32,990 --> 01:44:35,120
The thin and wholesome blood.
把我健康的血液彻底摧毁了

1323
01:44:35,140 --> 01:44:36,920
So did it mine.
我就这样被毒害了

1324
01:44:39,540 --> 01:44:42,590
A most instant tetter barked about...
转眼间我全身长满了烂疮...

1325
01:44:44,170 --> 01:44:48,190
...Most lazar-like, with vile and loathsome crust,
如癞病般浑身长满可憎的痂皮

1326
01:44:48,200 --> 01:44:50,790
All my smooth body.
体无完肤

1327
01:44:55,440 --> 01:44:56,940
Oh.
啊

1328
01:44:57,530 --> 01:44:59,330
Horrible.
惨呀

1329
01:45:01,310 --> 01:45:03,820
Oh, horrible. Most horrible.
哦 惨啊 太惨了

1330
01:45:03,840 --> 01:45:06,210
If thou hast nature in thee, bear it not...
只要你还有人性 就不要再忍了...

1331
01:45:06,220 --> 01:45:09,110
He has swapped places with our son.
他成了我们的儿子

1332
01:45:11,670 --> 01:45:13,540
Look at me.
回头看我

1333
01:45:19,990 --> 01:45:21,820
Look at me.
回头看我

1334
01:46:00,210 --> 01:46:04,900
The... the glowworm shows the matin to be near,
萤 萤火虫的微光已经暗淡

1335
01:46:04,910 --> 01:46:08,540
And 'gins to pale his uneffectual fires.
黎明就要来了

1336
01:46:29,130 --> 01:46:31,000
My boy.
我的儿子啊

1337
01:46:37,410 --> 01:46:39,010
Adieu.
再会了

1338
01:46:44,130 --> 01:46:45,730
Adieu.
再会了

1339
01:46:50,480 --> 01:46:51,720
Adieu.
再会了

1340
01:47:01,760 --> 01:47:03,290
Remember me.
记着我

1341
01:48:14,540 --> 01:48:17,620
To be, or not to be,
生存还是毁灭

1342
01:48:17,700 --> 01:48:19,490
that is the question.
这是个问题

1343
01:48:19,510 --> 01:48:21,630
Whether 'tis nobler in the mind to suffer
哪种更高贵？是默然忍受

1344
01:48:21,650 --> 01:48:24,610
The slings and arrows of outrageous fortune,
命运投来的巨石 射来的毒箭？

1345
01:48:24,620 --> 01:48:27,060
Or to take arms against a sea of troubles
还是挺身反抗汹涌的苦海

1346
01:48:27,080 --> 01:48:29,560
And, by opposing, end them.
通过斗争 渡向彼岸？

1347
01:48:30,530 --> 01:48:33,170
To die, to sleep,
死了 沉睡了

1348
01:48:33,250 --> 01:48:34,690
No more.
就那样了

1349
01:48:34,700 --> 01:48:36,940
And by a sleep, to say we end
要是一场睡眠可以终结

1350
01:48:36,950 --> 01:48:39,340
The heartache and the thousand natural shocks
我们这些血肉之躯生来要承受的

1351
01:48:39,360 --> 01:48:41,790
That flesh is heir to-- 'tis a consummation
万千苦难 那可是天大的好事

1352
01:48:41,810 --> 01:48:43,850
Devoutly to be wished.
是求之不得的结局

1353
01:48:46,340 --> 01:48:47,600
To die,
死了

1354
01:48:47,620 --> 01:48:49,440
To sleep, perchance to dream.
沉睡了 没准还有梦呢

1355
01:48:49,460 --> 01:48:51,530
Ay, there's the rub.
啊 这就是问题

1356
01:48:51,740 --> 01:48:54,330
For in that sleep of death, what dreams may come
摆脱了这凡尘肉体 在那死亡的沉睡中

1357
01:48:54,340 --> 01:48:56,120
When we have shuffled off this mortal coil
我们会做什么梦

1358
01:48:56,140 --> 01:48:58,710
Must give us pause.
这必然令人踌躇

1359
01:48:59,030 --> 01:49:00,230
There's the respect
正是这份顾虑

1360
01:49:00,250 --> 01:49:04,260
That makes calamity of so long life.
让我们心甘陷入这漫长的苦难

1361
01:49:04,440 --> 01:49:07,410
Who would bear the whips and scorns of time,
谁甘心忍受这人世的鞭挞和嘲辱

1362
01:49:07,420 --> 01:49:08,740
The oppressor's wrong,
压迫的屈辱

1363
01:49:08,750 --> 01:49:11,130
the proud man's contumely,
傲慢的蔑辱

1364
01:49:11,250 --> 01:49:14,340
The pangs of despised love,
心碎的羞辱

1365
01:49:14,350 --> 01:49:15,660
the law's delay,
法律的冷辱

1366
01:49:15,670 --> 01:49:17,580
The insolence of office, and the spurns
官吏的欺辱 以及小人对

1367
01:49:17,590 --> 01:49:19,820
That patient merit of the unworthy take,
勤勤恳恳老实人的侮辱

1368
01:49:19,840 --> 01:49:21,840
When he himself might his quietus make
否则当一把匕首就能解脱

1369
01:49:21,850 --> 01:49:23,410
With a bare bodkin?
谁不愿意？

1370
01:49:23,420 --> 01:49:24,970
Who would fardels bear,
谁愿背负这重担

1371
01:49:24,990 --> 01:49:27,410
To grunt and sweat under a weary life,
撑着这疲惫的身躯呻吟 流汗

1372
01:49:27,420 --> 01:49:30,250
But that the dread of something after death,
要不是死后那无人归返

1373
01:49:30,270 --> 01:49:32,540
The undiscovered country from whose bourn
未知的国度令我们恐惧

1374
01:49:32,550 --> 01:49:34,690
No traveler returns, puzzles the will,
困扰了我们的意志

1375
01:49:34,710 --> 01:49:36,940
And makes us rather bear those ills...
使我们宁愿忍受眼前的不幸...

1376
01:49:53,440 --> 01:49:55,020
En garde!
各就各位

1377
01:50:19,640 --> 01:50:20,640
One!
一剑

1378
01:50:20,670 --> 01:50:23,030
No! No!
不 没有击中

1379
01:50:24,110 --> 01:50:26,280
A hit, a palpable hit!
中了 很明显的一剑

1380
01:50:26,300 --> 01:50:28,690
Our son shall win!
我们的儿子一定会胜利

1381
01:50:28,700 --> 01:50:31,480
- Well, again! - Gertrude, do not drink.
- 好吧 再来 - 格特鲁德 别喝

1382
01:50:50,290 --> 01:50:52,530
Another hit! What say you?
又是一剑 你自己说中没中

1383
01:51:01,440 --> 01:51:03,350
Have at you now!
吃我一剑

1384
01:51:31,850 --> 01:51:34,180
How does the queen?
王后怎么了？

1385
01:51:34,190 --> 01:51:35,910
She swoons to see them bleed.
她肯定是晕血了

1386
01:51:35,930 --> 01:51:39,450
No, no, the drink, the drink!
不 不 是那酒 那酒

1387
01:51:39,460 --> 01:51:41,530
Oh, my dear Hamlet.
啊 我心爱的哈姆雷特

1388
01:51:41,550 --> 01:51:43,070
I am poisoned.
我中毒了

1389
01:51:45,320 --> 01:51:47,790
Oh, villainy!
啊 恶毒的阴谋

1390
01:51:47,800 --> 01:51:50,400
Ho, let the door be locked!
喂 把门锁上

1391
01:51:50,680 --> 01:51:52,580
Treachery! Seek it out!
奸贼 揪出来

1392
01:51:52,730 --> 01:51:54,510
It is here, Hamlet.
哈姆雷特 奸贼就在这儿

1393
01:51:56,480 --> 01:51:58,280
Hamlet, thou art slain.
哈姆雷特 你也要死了

1394
01:51:58,300 --> 01:52:00,590
No medicine in the world can do thee good.
没有药能救得了你

1395
01:52:00,750 --> 01:52:03,080
In thee, there is not half an hour's life.
你活不到半个钟头了

1396
01:52:03,670 --> 01:52:05,290
The king's to blame!
都是国王做的孽

1397
01:52:08,090 --> 01:52:09,940
The point envenomed, too?
剑头也有毒药？

1398
01:52:09,950 --> 01:52:11,830
Then, venom, to thy work!
那么好 毒药 也给你

1399
01:52:22,860 --> 01:52:28,610
Here, thou incestuous, murderous, damned Dane!
你这个乱伦的 血腥的丹麦的魔王

1400
01:52:30,270 --> 01:52:31,870
Drink...
给我喝...

1401
01:52:31,890 --> 01:52:34,220
Drink off this potion!
喝下这杯毒酒

1402
01:52:36,280 --> 01:52:38,830
Is thy union here?
你那心爱的珍珠在里面吗？

1403
01:52:36,280 --> 01:52:38,840
{\an8}【心爱的珍珠: 具双关 既指原著中的珍珠 又指婚姻】

1404
01:52:38,860 --> 01:52:42,030
Follow my mother.
跟我的母亲一道去吧

1405
01:53:07,960 --> 01:53:09,290
I am dead.
我死了

1406
01:53:12,840 --> 01:53:14,440
Thou livest.
可你还活着

1407
01:53:15,680 --> 01:53:17,750
Report me and my cause aright
请将我的故事与大义

1408
01:53:17,770 --> 01:53:19,850
To the unsatisfied.
如实告知尚不知情的人吧

1409
01:53:19,860 --> 01:53:21,970
If thou didst ever hold me in thy heart,
若你曾对我怀有深情与敬重

1410
01:53:21,980 --> 01:53:24,220
Absent thee from felicity awhile,
暂且别去享那极乐

1411
01:53:24,240 --> 01:53:28,300
And in this harsh world draw thy breath in pain
留在这残酷的尘世 隐忍着痛苦

1412
01:53:28,340 --> 01:53:30,380
To tell my story.
去把我的故事讲清

1413
01:53:48,340 --> 01:53:51,380
Ah, I die!
啊 我要死了

1414
01:54:00,170 --> 01:54:04,140
The potent poison quite o'ercrows my spirit.
这剧毒正夺去我的意志

1415
01:55:21,890 --> 01:55:24,660
The rest is silence.
余下的只有沉寂

